Answer to the question.  You needn't post if academies weren't included.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Some SDA schools (and Columbia Union College in particular) have large </i><br>
<i>&gt; enough minority populations that (Anglo) parents do not want to send </i><br>
<i>&gt; their children there and are sending them to other colleges instead.</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt; 1)  Is this happening at any local SDA schools that you know of?</i><br>
<p>
Is this supposed to include academies as well?  There was a dwindling<br>
white population at Takoma Academy (where I attended 4 years ago).<br>
They often went to Highland View or Shenandoah boarding academies <br>
instead though.  TA, located within the DC beltway, is becoming more<br>
and more of an inner city school.  I think the reasoning stemmed quite <br>
a bit from that.  Kinda the idea of, if you have the money, keep the<br>
kids out of the higher danger zone.<br>
<p>
<pre>
