<title>Mar_1993: White flight from SDA schools</title>
<h1>White flight from SDA schools</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Sat,  6 Mar 1993 16:02:48 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#70">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#70">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#70">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#70">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0071.html">bluejay@dcs.qmw.ac.uk: "Re: SDA-L: Michael Card"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0069.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re Pacifism"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0072.html">Lisa Parry: "Re: White flight from SDA schools"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In the past few months, a conversation with a high-level church administrator<br>
on the topic of race relations yielded the following point:<br>
<p>
Some SDA schools (and Columbia Union College in particular) have large <br>
enough minority populations that (Anglo) parents do not want to send <br>
their children there and are sending them to other colleges instead.<br>
<p>
Questions:<br>
<p>
1)  Is this happening at any local SDA schools that you know of?<br>
<p>
2)  If it is happening, is it due to racism or just white SDA's abandoning <br>
SDA schools all together?<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
