<!-- body="start" -->
I have not heard the news, but yesterday there was an article in the<br>
paper about this.  They identified the cult as Davidians, a branch offshoot<br>
of the 7th day Adventist church, that moved it's headquarters to waco in<br>
1935.  The current leader, claims that he is Christ.  The cult was heavily<br>
armed, and belives that thier 24 year old leader is the only one who can<br>
open the 7 seals of revalation.  He claims to have been married since 1984<br>
and has 2 children.  However, former members of the cult, say that he has<br>
bragged about having sex with underaged children, and has fathered many<br>
of the commune's children.  I was going to post the entire contents of the<br>
article, but left it at home.  Last night was the pits.  I worked about<br>
6 hours trying to straighted up the plumbing in my house, and still don't<br>
have water, so was quite tired and distracted this morning.<br>
<p>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
