<title>Mar_1993: Re: Shootout in Texas</title>
<h1>Re: Shootout in Texas</h1>
<i>CHRMD@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i><br>
<i>02 Mar 1993 12:30:22 +1100</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#3">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#3">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#3">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#3">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0004.html">Harvey Brenneise: "Why go to the seminary"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0002.html">Woody Baker: "Re: Shootout in Texas"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Yesterday when I read all the comments about a shootout in Texas I can't<br>
say I was expecting to hear any more about it than what I'd heard on the<br>
net. But cult violence is cult violence and has worldwide appeal. So when<br>
I watched the news last night (Monday) I was interested to note that there<br>
was some time spent on the issue. (I didn't notice any associations of the<br>
group to SDAs though.)<br>
<p>
What I did notice was that it was of particular interest to Australians<br>
because there were two Australians amongst the group. They showed pictures<br>
of these twins Nicole and Peter, then they showed an interview with the<br>
leader from last year (claiming he was Christ and talking about guns etc)<br>
then they came back to "the Gents" - the parents of Nicole and Peter. <br>
<p>
That was when it hit me. I knew Nicole.<br>
<p>
I don't usually see people that I know on the 6 o'clock news! Nicole<br>
was a first year student at Avondale College with me in 1987. She lived<br>
just down the hall in the dormitory. I have a picture of her in my<br>
photo album, sitting with a whole bunch of other girls in my room.<br>
<p>
Then she left College. No one could talk her out of going. We all wondered<br>
how we had failed her. One girl took a worship one night talking about<br>
Nicole and saying how she would show real interest in spiritual things and<br>
ask deep questions but everyone was too busy being superficial and trendy to<br>
take any of that seriously.<br>
<p>
So now I hear of Nicole again - and I feel a bit shook-up!<br>
<p>
Does anyone else know anyone caught up in such a thing?<br>
Why do people get involved in such groups?<br>
<p>
Raylene<br>
---*---<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
