Have you tried the Archie server that was developed out of McGill U in<br>
Canada.  I forget how to actually talk to one of the archie servers.  We<br>
have links to it in our gopher server that I use.  If you know what you<br>
are looking for you can try searching for it with archie.<br>
<p>
If you can't find archie or a gopher search option, you can telnet to<br>
edmund.cs.andrews.edu and login in as library (there is no password).<br>
This will put you directly into gopher.  Option 10 from the top level<br>
menu is searches.  From the searches menu, you can search for an exact<br>
name with option 1 or a substring match in option 7.  I use option 7,<br>
the substring match myself, just in case there are version numbers<br>
tacked on the end or something.<br>
