<title>Mar_1993: Serving without a degree</title>
<h1>Serving without a degree</h1>
<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i><br>
<i>02 Mar 1993 15:19:01 +1100</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#9">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#9">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#9">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#9">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0010.html">HARRISP@UTKVX.UTCC.UTK.EDU: "Texas Shootout--SDA Link"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0008.html">sdanet@peter.cs.andrews.edu: "Re: FTP and Mail Server List"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I found it interesting to read Harvey's comments about various attitudes<br>
held by seminary students. It seems that some things are the same no <br>
matter which half of the world you live in (at least in Western society).<br>
<p>
At Avondale College there is always a percentage of ministerial students<br>
who feel that they were called by God to minister, and so why should any<br>
academic requirement stand between them and their calling. Some of these<br>
guys find the more esoteric subjects very difficult, and many do not have<br>
a strong academic background. There are always casualties along the way,<br>
students who feel strongly called and yet can't pass Greek II or Systematic<br>
Theology or whatever.<br>
<p>
I have often wondered why God only ever seems to call people to be <br>
official church leaders. Surely a person doesn't have to have a degree<br>
to be a spiritual leader, and surely a person can be a spiritual leader<br>
without being the pastor. I would like to see some of those who feel <br>
called to be leaders take on that responsibility as best they can in<br>
their current state, whether they're plumbers or professors. A call<br>
to minister doesn't equate with a call to the seminary.<br>
<p>
Those are my thoughts, anyway. What do you think?<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0010.html">HARRISP@UTKVX.UTCC.UTK.EDU: "Texas Shootout--SDA Link"</a>
