<title>Mar_1993: church image</title>
<h1>church image</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue,  2 Mar 1993 17:19:58 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#11">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#11">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#11">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#11">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0012.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Matthew 24"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0010.html">HARRISP@UTKVX.UTCC.UTK.EDU: "Texas Shootout--SDA Link"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Just a comment on the Davidian cult and bad press for SDA Church.  The LDS<br>
church has suffered many times when fanatical extremist polygamist groups<br>
appear in the news.  (The cult that killed two federal agents about 3 years<br>
ago after bombing an LDS chapel. The LeBarons.)  The general public typically<br>
picks up on fanatical cults and automatically equates their views with the<br>
church from which they split.  The next time SDAs think about the LDS church<br>
and associate it with polygamist cults, remember this experience with the<br>
Davidians and the SDA Church.<br>
<p>
A thoughtful study of other churches and what they really believe will avoid<br>
a lot of misconceptions and misunderstandings.<br>
<p>
Cheryl<br>
<p>
<p>
[With this message Cheryl signed off the net.  She will not see your<br>
replies to this.  SCT]<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
