I have been reading this discussion of the seminary with some interest. <br>
It must be noted that although most go to the seminary for their MDiv,<br>
some do go there for other degrees in upper level theological studies. <br>
Last year I was sturggling with the notion of what I was going to do after<br>
I graduated from Iowa.  Should I go to beSeminary for an MDiv.  I<br>
realizied that that was not for me.  Instead I have felt called to go to<br>
seminary to get an M.A. in Religion.  I guess my point is that not all<br>
those going to Seminary and "called" as such maybe be there for a<br>
minsterial degree. <br>
Ian.<br>
