<!-- body="start" -->
[Steve, if you see more than one of these, no problem skipping mine.]<br>
<p>
March 2, 1993, Arizona Republic quotes AP's Scott Rothschild on the<br>
continuing stand-off near Waco, front-page continuing on second.<br>
Final 3 paragraphs in the article:<br>
<p>
    At 18, Koresh, who changed his name from Vernon Howell, joined<br>
    the Seventh-day Adventists in Tyler and was expelled two years later.<br>
<p>
    "We are not surprised at what happened in Waco," said Lynn Ray,<br>
    a church elder.<br>
<p>
    Cyril Miller, president of the church's Southwestern Union<br>
    Theological Center in Burleson, said, "He was a kook, a genuine<br>
    religious fanatic that [sic] was almost totally irrational."<br>
<p>
Anyone know who Lynn Ray is?  A SDA local church elder in Tyler?  Elsewhere?<br>
An elder in the Davidians or Branch Davidians?  By "church elder" did the<br>
writer perhaps mean an SDA leader in denominational employ?<br>
<p>
I don't recognize the name Cyril Miller nor a Southwestern Union<br>
Theological Center nor anything SDA in Burleson.  Is this an erroneous<br>
reference to Southwestern Adventist College in Keene?<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola, 2900 S Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ 85282  "Canajun, eh?"
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  ".. I have set before you Life and Death, blessing and cursing;  therefore
      choose Life, that both you and your children may live"  Deut 30:19
[As I recall, Burleson is a) near Keene b) the home of the Southwestern
Union offices (visible from I-35W).  SCT]
</pre>
