<title>Mar_1993: Gen Con News Release about Waco, TX</title>
<h1>Gen Con News Release about Waco, TX</h1>
Daniel R. Bidwell (<i>bidwell@peter.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 3 Mar 1993 00:00:06 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#24">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#24">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#24">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#24">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0025.html">Lisa Parry: "Re: AZ Republic/AP on Howell/Koresh"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0023.html">Daniel R. Bidwell: "Re: AZ Republic/AP on Howell/Koresh"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
This is a copy of the news GC news release as is being distributed at<br>
Andrews University to the faculty and staff.<br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; The following is a news release from the General Conference concerning the</i><br>
<i>&gt; incident in Waco, Texas:</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Waco, Texas, Group Has No Connection with Seventh-day Adventist Church</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt;      SILVER SPRING, MD--"Branch Davidians" in the news today have no </i><br>
<i>&gt; connection with the Seventh-day Adventist Church.</i><br>
<i>&gt;      Several Splinter groups away from Victor Houteff who was disfellowshipped</i><br>
<i>&gt; from the Seventh-day Adventist Church and its ministry at Los Angeles in 1929.</i><br>
<i>&gt; Vernon Howell assumed leadership of the current Waco group in 1988 after being</i><br>
<i>&gt; acquitted following a shoot-out with George Roden.</i><br>
<i>&gt;      The 1988 gun battle was in dispute of the Mount Carmel property near Waco,</i><br>
<i>&gt; Texas, which George said was his, following the death of his father Ben in 1978.</i><br>
<i>&gt;      Through the years, the group--which has changed leaders and membership as</i><br>
<i>&gt; further splinters were developed--have called themselves The Shepherd's Rod,</i><br>
<i>&gt; Davidian Seventh-day Adventists, Branch Davidians, and The Davidians.  Not</i><br>
<i>&gt; one of them is know to hold membership in a Seventh-day Adventist Church at</i><br>
<i>&gt; Waco or any other place.  Howell was disfellowshipped from the Tyler, Texas,</i><br>
<i>&gt; congregation in 1981.</i><br>
<i>&gt;      Leaders of the various groups have included Victor Houteff's widow</i><br>
<i>&gt; Florence, Ben roden, Lois Roden, George Roden, and Vernon Howell.</i><br>
<i>&gt;      Seventh-day Adventist total more than seven million in 206 countries</i><br>
<i>&gt; worldwide.  They promote the sanctity of the family, practice allegiance to</i><br>
<i>&gt; government, observe the seventh-day (Saturday) Sabbath, believe in a second</i><br>
<i>&gt; advent of Christ, follow a non-violent lifestyle, and acknowledge Christ as</i><br>
<i>&gt; the Judge of the universe.  </i><br>
<i>&gt;      While North American membership exceeds 783,000, about nine of every</i><br>
<i>&gt; ten Adventists live in other nations.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; 				     Released by Shirley Burton on</i><br>
<i>&gt; 						 February 28, 1993</i><br>
<i>&gt; -- </i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Jolie M. High</i><br>
<i>&gt; Computer Science Secretary</i><br>
<i>&gt; phone:  (616) 471-3516</i><br>
<i>&gt; e-mail: high@andrews.edu</i><br>
<i>&gt; Office Hours:  8:30 am - 12:30 pm and 1:30 pm - 5:30 pm</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; "STRESS" that confusion created when one's mind overrides the body's basic</i><br>
<i>&gt; 	 desire to choke the living you-know-what out of some you-know-who</i><br>
<i>&gt; 	 who desperately needs it!</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<p>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
Daniel R. Bidwell	|	bidwell@andrews.edu
Andrews University	Computer Science &amp; Information Systems Department
If two always agree, one of them is unnecesary
"Friends don't let friends do DOS"
