<title>Mar_1993: Who is Lynn Ray?</title>
<h1>Who is Lynn Ray?</h1>
<i>HARRISP@UTKVX.UTCC.UTK.EDU</i><br>
<i>03 Mar 1993 10:41:15 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#29">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#29">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#29">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#29">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0030.html">Nancy Vyhmeister: "M.A.in Religion"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0028.html">Fred Kinsey: "Re: AZ Republic/AP on Howell/Koresh"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Lynn Ray, quoted in versions of the Keresh story as being from Tyler,<br>
Texas, was an active member when I lived there in the mid-1980s. He is<br>
a successful businessman with no ties whatsoever to the Davidians, but a<br>
regular member of the Tyler SDA Church. <br>
<p>
Does anyone know if Shirley Burton (Communications Director for the SDA<br>
Church) has an e-mail address?<br>
<p>
Pam Harris<br>
Harrisp@utkvx.utk.edu<br>
