<title>Mar_1993: M.A.in Religion</title>
<h1>M.A.in Religion</h1>
Nancy Vyhmeister (<i>vyhmeist@susan.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 3 Mar 1993 13:47:13 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#30">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#30">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#30">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#30">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0031.html">Malachi Robertson: "Waco group"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0029.html">HARRISP@UTKVX.UTCC.UTK.EDU: "Who is Lynn Ray?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
FYI  The M.A. in Religion is an academic degree.  It may be taken in one<br>
year if the candidate has a B.A. Theology.  Otherwise it takes 2 years.<br>
Its main purpose is to prepare candidates for entrance into Ph.D.<br>
programs.  The degree is offered in NT, OT, Theology, and Mission.<br>
It is not ministerial preparation, since there are no practics.<br>
The M.Div. program is designed to train pastors who are facing a most<br>
demanding calling and profession--being all things to all people, and<br>
above all, responsible to God.  It takes 27 months and includes <br>
practical responsibilities in a church, as well as theoretical courses<br>
in pastoring.<br>
<p>
Nancy<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
