<title>Mar_1993: Branch Davidians</title>
<h1>Branch Davidians</h1>
Lenson Wong (<i>lenson@ocf.berkeley.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 3 Mar 1993 12:57:18 -0800</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#32">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#32">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#32">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#32">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0033.html">Woody Baker: "Re: Branch SDA's"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0031.html">Malachi Robertson: "Waco group"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Last night on the MacNeil-Lehrer News Hour, a Professor at UC Santa<br>
Barbara who is an expert on cults was interviewed concerning the origin<br>
of the Branch Davidians and specifically concerning their relationship<br>
to the SDA Church. He said that in 1942 a group of SDA's objected<br>
to the Church's relaxing of their pacifist stand toward WWII. This <br>
group felt that the Church should hold a stronger pacifist stand (I assume<br>
tis relates to participation in the military.). They then broke off<br>
from the Church and formed the Branch Davidians. This is the first<br>
that I've heards this story. Does anyone know if this is true?<br>
<p>
<p>
Lenson Wong<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
