<!-- body="start" -->
What ever the case, the deeper question is how is the church going to<br>
approach damage contorol.  I noticed that on the news this morning, the<br>
reporter went out of his way to "make it completely clear that this group<br>
has nothing to do with the current Seventh-day Adventist church"  It sounds<br>
like damage control is engaged, and working.  One of my co-workers (a very<br>
good friend), who is very aquainted with the SDA church, having gone through<br>
a Revelation Seminar, and known a SDA pastor very well, walked into my cube<br>
and jokingly told me that my phone had been ringing, and he thought about<br>
answering it, and saying that I was up in a compound in Waco, and no one<br>
knew what I was doing.  Later he came by and ribbed me about "my folks<br>
up in Waco".  I happen to know this guy very well, so I took it for what it<br>
was, a bit of joking.  He had taken the time to go to the library sunday<br>
and researched the Branch Davidian's, and gave me a run down on the history.<br>
We had a good visit, but it still was uncomfortable, and I wonder just how<br>
many other incidents, both joking and serious have happened to others.<br>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
