<!-- body="start" -->
I only saw one mention of this on the SDANet.  The Frederick Maryland church<br>
burned down last Sunday.  The timing of this event was enough to make the fire<br>
department suspect arson, but on Monday they determined that the fire was<br>
started by a faulty transformer.<br>
<p>
These days is not uncommon for churches to be fire bombed.  There was some<br>
concern that the events in Texas would cause someone to bomb one of our<br>
churches.  There have been some threats.  I don't know if there were any new<br>
threats after the events last Sunday or not.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
