I just read in the newsmagazine "Newsweek", that Pope Pius XII is on the road<br>
to canonization. There is uproar over this because Pius "(who reigned from 1939<br>
to '58) was publicly silent during the Holocaust."  I must confess my <br>
ignorance<br>
on this... what is canonization?<br>
<p>
[Canonization is the process of the Catholic church declaring a person <br>
to be a saint.  SCT]<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
