Well Woody, I also have had comments re this Texas shootout.<br>
<p>
There is one other Christian (besides myself) in the Chemistry Department. He<br>
used to be caught up in a very legalistic offshoot of the Presbyterian(?)<br>
church (as a minister) but left.<br>
<p>
Yesterday he was making comments to the effect that "Well I suppose you must<br>
have had a lot of questions about the Texas shooting?". (And apart from him<br>
I hadn't). I replied to the effect that I hadn't (and why should I have <br>
anyway) and he started with the breakaway from the SDA church story. (I'm<br>
sure this guy things SDA's are really weird). But fortunately I had read<br>
lots of history of the cult in SDAnet so could answer his claims with some<br>
degree of knowledge! <br>
<p>
I almost get the impression that it is the other Christians that think we're<br>
weird more than people without any religion at all - or maybe the others are<br>
just more polite?!<br>
<p>
Raylene<br>
---*---<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
