<title>Mar_1993: the EGW CD-ROM:  price? performance?</title>
<h1>the EGW CD-ROM:  price? performance?</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 4 Mar 93 11:51:27 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#44">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#44">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#44">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#44">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0045.html">Marcus Stringer: "Re: Branch SDA's"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0043.html">Fred Christiansen: "re: Branch Davidians"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Any users of the EGW CD-ROM?  Whatzit cost?  Is it worth it or would you,<br>
to someone contemplating its purchase, recommend sticking with the 3<br>
volume index?  How well done is the search &amp; display software?  How would<br>
it compare to Bible search &amp; display software such as QuickVerse,<br>
PC Study Bible, or OnLine Bible, in terms of interface, ease-of-use?<br>
<p>
Finally, any CD-ROM drives to recommend or avoid?  DAK claims to have<br>
good ones for relatively low $$.  Thx.<br>
