<!-- body="start" -->
A coworker of mine, made it a point to stop by my office yesterday.<br>
He's from a Catholic (dad)/Jewish (mom) home, and is disillusioned<br>
about religion in general.  We had a good visit, and he shared some<br>
jokes about "Kooks" in religion, making a special point to say that<br>
he didn't believe the SDA church was "Kookie".  Then we fell into a<br>
discussion about the lack of coverage (in comparison) over the World<br>
Trade Center bombing.  Ultimately concluding that all these "Davidian"<br>
ethnic cleansing, legalizing mistreatment of other people, are but<br>
*symptoms* of the diseases of pride, greed, and self-exaltation = hearts<br>
without the testimony, and passion for JESUS and his love.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
