Hello fellow netters.  I have never posted anything on the net, but I sit back<br>
and listen to a lot.  I'm currently a student at the University of Maryland<br>
seeking a degree in computer science.  I'm a baby SDA for I joined the church<br>
about 4 years ago. <br>
<p>
Actually, I'm making this post for a friend of mine, Richard Kajiura, who <br>
works at the Communications Department for the General Conference under the<br>
supervision of Shirley Burton.  He was wanting some responses to the following<br>
question.<br>
<p>
  We were all created in God's image, what does this mean to you?<br>
<p>
The answer should be in 60 words or less.  Approximately 5 responses will be<br>
chosen to be put into the NAD Adventist Review which is the monthly issue<br>
which goes to most North American Adventist homes.  He needs the responses by<br>
March 10.  If your article is chosen, the Review will be wanting a picture<br>
of you to be printed along with your response.  This is actually an experi-<br>
mental posting, for the Communications Department is considering subscribing<br>
to CompuServe for further posts of this nature.  Your responses are valuable<br>
so the Review staff can see the value of Internet mail and it's uses.  You<br>
should also include your full name and telephone number with area code so<br>
the Review staff can contact you if you are picked.  Because of this, you<br>
may want to mail your responses directly to me.  <br>
<p>
Thanks,<br>
 Tony L. Donley<br>
 caesar@eng.umd.edu<br>
