<!-- body="start" -->
-----------------------Marcus Stringer writes:------------------------<br>
A coworker of mine, made it a point to stop by my office yesterday.<br>
He's from a Catholic (dad)/Jewish (mom) home, and is disillusioned<br>
about religion in general.  We had a good visit, and he shared some<br>
jokes about "Kooks" in religion, making a special point to say that<br>
he didn't believe the SDA church was "Kookie".  Then we fell into a<br>
discussion about the lack of coverage (in comparison) over the World<br>
Trade Center bombing.  Ultimately concluding that all these "Davidian"<br>
ethnic cleansing, legalizing mistreatment of other people, are but<br>
*symptoms* of the diseases of pride, greed, and self-exaltation = hearts<br>
without the testimony, and passion for JESUS and his love.<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
That lack of coverage is apparent here too, in fact, the Waco shootout<br>
has eclipsed almost every other foreign news story of its type, even<br>
the events in the Balkans or Somalia. There's something in the papers<br>
*every* day about the Waco incident. Yesterday there was more than 1 page<br>
of articles abouut the Brach Davidians and also other "cults", and the<br>
SDA church was mentioned more than i like, although they didn't call us a<br>
cult. It seems that stories of cults interest the public a lot.<br>
	Well, as for that bit about it being symptoms of a godless heart,<br>
its quite true, in fact you only have to look around and watch people to<br>
see all that stuff. There is so much selfishness, ruthlessness and hostility<br>
and distrust in this world, its rotten to the core, thats why we have a song<br>
called "This world is not my home" because we can't feel at home here.<br>
	Education and legislation, culture and society, these all have their<br>
sphere of influence and use, but when it comes to transforming the heart,<br>
changing the character, implanting right motives, morality and altruism,<br>
these are all of little effect and God is THE ONLY answer.<br>
	Well, like your friend, its easy to get disillusioned with religion,<br>
because most of it is indistinguishable from the darkness of this blighted<br>
world, but all who seek the truth honestly shall find it.<br>
<p>
	-beng<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
