<title>Mar_1993: Battle Creek Aventist Hospital</title>
<h1>Battle Creek Aventist Hospital</h1>
Tim Swensen (<i>swensen@ecn.purdue.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 5 Mar 93 11:10:22 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#54">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#54">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#54">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#54">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0055.html">Dan Gill: "EGW CD-ROM"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0053.html">ronswen@aol.com: "Re: Under Law"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0267.html">DOWE001%TSU.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu: "Re: Battle Creek Aventist Hospital"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
SDAnet,<br>
<p>
The news regarding Battle Creek Adventist Hospital (BCAH) is not surprising.<br>
My mother has worked there for about 20 years.  I worked there during academy.<br>
Mom recently was forced to retire due job cuts there in January.  She is not <br>
in any way bitter toward BCAH.  It was a good place to work.  I rather enjoyed <br>
it there myself, although I wouldn't want to scrub pots and pans for a living<br>
the rest of my days. :)<br>
<p>
It really is a shame to see the Hospital's fortunes wane.  It continues to <br>
provide a necessary service to southwestern Michigan.  Unfortunately, while<br>
the services may be needed, the money is not available to pay for them.  <br>
<p>
I have not worked there for quite some time, so am not qualified to comment<br>
on the current spiritual climate of the care given there.  The question needs<br>
to raised (and is almost certainly being discussed by BCAH administrators):<br>
Can BCAH fulfill its mission if not owned or controlled by SDA's?<br>
<p>
This would be a good time to examine on the net just what we mean by <br>
"distinctive Adventist health care."  I need to look into this myself.  The <br>
latest Adventist Review (March 4, NAD edition) caries an article by Robert <br>
Folkenberg regarding Adventist health care.  This is a good place to start.<br>
<p>
I have a lot of good memories from Battle Creek.  They are in a significant<br>
way related to the many people employed there over the years, not to mention<br>
the other institutions in the area which, in part, serve the families of those<br>
employees.  Battle Creek Academy will suffer if BCAH closes.<br>
<p>
Maybe my brother Ron, who is also a Battle Creek Academy alumnus, can add to<br>
the discussion.<br>
<p>
Tim Swensen<br>
swensen@ecn.purdue.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
