<title>Mar_1993: the EGW CD-ROM: price? performance?</title>
<h1>the EGW CD-ROM: price? performance?</h1>
Cam Litvin (<i>cameron@tekgen.bv.tek.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 5 Mar 93 10:06:30 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#57">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#57">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#57">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#57">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0058.html">davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com: "Re: Under Law"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0056.html">Bruce Holm: "Re:  Thoughts on the Waco standoff"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;Fred Christiansen, Motorola, 2900 S Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ 85282  "Canajun,</i><br>
<i>&gt;eh?"  Writes...</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;Any users of the EGW CD-ROM?  Whatzit cost?  Is it worth it or would you,</i><br>
<i>&gt;to someone contemplating its purchase, recommend sticking with the 3</i><br>
<i>&gt;volume index?  How well done is the search &amp; display software?  How would</i><br>
<i>&gt;it compare to Bible search &amp; display software such as QuickVerse,</i><br>
<i>&gt;PC Study Bible, or OnLine Bible, in terms of interface, ease-of-use?</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;Finally, any CD-ROM drives to recommend or avoid?  DAK claims to have</i><br>
<i>&gt;good ones for relatively low $$.  Thx.</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<p>
I recently purchased the EGW CD-ROM.  I paid around $425, but I had a $50<br>
discount that was on a back page of the Review about 4-5 months ago.  I<br>
believe the discount was available through March of this year so look for<br>
it.  I think the search feature works well and is reasonably fast.  I<br>
prefer the Windows program to the DOS program.  My system is a 386/40,<br>
Diamond Stealth Video Card (this improved screen speed), NEC-25 CD-ROM<br>
drive (it was packaged with a sound card and speakers, Media Vision's<br>
Fusion CD product).  I've seen the DAK inexpensive CD product and it is<br>
probably comparable.  I was concerned about the EGW CD-ROM and CD-ROM drive<br>
compatibility, but the latest drives appear to have settled on current<br>
drive standards so have no problems.  I've purchased a variety of CD-ROM's<br>
since with no compatibility problems.<br>
<p>
I'm very happy with the CD-ROM.  Not being a bookworm, having the<br>
computer do the searching form me has helped tremendously.  As I said I<br>
prefer the Windows search program.  It's good, but parts of the<br>
program could be better.  BTW, by getting the CD-ROM now, you are suppose<br>
to get the next upgrade free.<br>
<p>
Cam<br>
<p>
