<title>Mar_1993: Church vs. State News</title>
<h1>Church vs. State News</h1>
Marcus Stringer (<i>marcuss@microsoft.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri,  5 Mar 93 14:21:56 PST </i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#60">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#60">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#60">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#60">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0061.html">Bruce Holm: "Re: Battle Creek Adventist Hospital in Trouble"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0059.html">Steven Timm: "Citizen Alliance Religious Groups"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
This is either from the Denver Post or the Boulder Daily Camera<br>
<p>
Embattled minister takes to airwaves<br>
<p>
LAPORTE -- A LaPorte minister has begun broadcasting nightly sermons via<br>
shortwave radio from his church after the state seized the church's property<br>
in a squabble over an election law violation.<br>
        Pete Peters and supporter Steve Wray have been sleeping at the<br>
LaPorte Church of Christ since it was seized Friday.  Peters remained at the<br>
church Wednesday.<br>
        The state says Peters owes $10,115 in fines for sponsoring political<br>
ads without registering as a political action committee.<br>
        Peters said he doubts the state will stop at seizing church property.<br>
 ----------<br>
Pete Peters is said to be the author of "Death Penalty for Homosexuals,"<br>
It is also being questioned if he is affiliated with one of the White<br>
Supremacist groups (White Aryan Resistance?).  He actually gets 30 minutes a<br>
week of air time here in the Bay Area (Sunday Mornings on KPLA-AM (770) from<br>
9:30 to 10:00).  Last week he explained how high taxes are caused by<br>
America's refusal to condemn homosexuality...<br>
<p>
Does anyone in Colorado know more about this?<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
