<title>Mar_1993: re: Reformed SDA members and my local church (more detail)</title>
<h1>re: Reformed SDA members and my local church (more detail)</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 5 Mar 93 15:47:37 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#63">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#63">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#63">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#63">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0064.html">Trevor Tompkins: "Re: Thoughts on the Waco standoff"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0062.html">Fred Christiansen: "wisdom from a youth"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[Fred Christiansen writes:]<br>
<i>&gt; The background for my info is this:  In 1987, a family moved to this</i><br>
<i>&gt; area and started attending our church.  They were members of the Reformed</i><br>
<i>&gt; SDA church.  During an elders meeting, the pastor discussed with us re</i><br>
<i>&gt; how to handle the application for membership in our church.  We moved</i><br>
<i>&gt; to Oregon before they were brought into membership, so I don't know the</i><br>
<i>&gt; rest of the details, [..]</i><br>
<p>
A friend's question let me know that I left things hanging more unclear<br>
than I intended.  By "rest of the details", I meant that I did not know<br>
by what means they were brought into membership; that is, whether it was<br>
delicate or straightforward (there are elders from my local church who<br>
are on this list who would know).  Suffice it to say that they (the family)<br>
are active members and make a valued contribution (especially taking on the<br>
youth group 8-).<br>
