<!-- body="start" -->
Oh soul are you weary and troubled,<br>
no light in the darkness you see?<br>
Theres light when you look at the Savior,<br>
and light more abundant and free!<br>
<p>
Turn your eyes upon Jesus, look FULL<br>
in his *wonderful* face.<br>
And the things of earth will grow strangely<br>
dim, in the light of _his_ glory and grace.<br>
=================================<br>
Your post is so true.  Not only do we go downhill when we keep our eyes on the<br>
unconverted "world", but even *more* dangerously, we go downhill looking at<br>
our moral deeds, worshiping our self-supplied righteousness (filthy rags)<br>
THINKING that we are on our way to heaven.<br>
<p>
It's exciting to remember that Jesus is so high, that we can't get over him.<br>
He's so low, that we can't crawl under him.  And he's so wide, that we can't<br>
sneak around him.  When all of our hee-hawing is over, we must face _Him_.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
