David B wrote _Much_  :  )<br>
======================<br>
Thanks for the post.  I can now locate some texts which have eluded me<br>
for some time... I'd like to add something.<br>
<p>
THE LAW:<br>
God said...<br>
<p>
Don't worship things, self, or other people, only worship me - because I'm<br>
the lover of your soul - worshiping things will make you greedy, selfish,<br>
and you'll try to be self-sufficient.  I've made you so that you need me.<br>
<p>
Please, don't even worship the symbols I've made... for they only to<br>
_point _ to me.  Worship _me_, I'm jealous for your attention.  Worshiping the<br>
symbols will make them more like curses than the blessings they were<br>
intended to be.<br>
<p>
Don't misuse my name.  Don't be careless with it, or you'll be guilty.<br>
You're a Christian, so don't go out of this house talking and living in<br>
opposition to my motives, my underlying principles and my character.<br>
<p>
Remember our family time.  I've marked the day... it's special.<br>
This reminds us all of our relation.  We belong to each other, as I continue<br>
explaining in the rules below....<br>
<p>
Be respectful to your parents, for they gave you birth!  Even when you<br>
disagree, or go separate ways - remember they aren't just any ole' people,<br>
they're your *parents*.  Have integrity, stand up for something, or you'll<br>
fall for anything.  Better yet, think well about what you stand for.  I know<br>
you'll make them proud, and if not, then you'll make _me_ proud.<br>
<p>
I'm not going to tolerate any murdering.  Your business isn't to cleans<br>
each other off the face of the earth.  I'm going to show you later, in greater<br>
detail, why this is so important.  The way this works is that even if you hate<br>
your brother, you have already murdered in your heart.  You don't even have<br>
to hate or swing the bat, just fail to stand against it, and you will <br>
be just as<br>
guilty.  Don't kill his drive to better himself in this life or in the <br>
life to come.<br>
We are going to love each other and in _this_ family.  Oh, I forgot, because<br>
we're members of this family, we are going to love those who don't love us,<br>
do good to people who do bad to us, pray for those who use us....<br>
<p>
I don't want you, hopping from spouse to spouse, spitting upon the covenants<br>
you make to each other.  They are supposed to reflect my covenant, my<br>
relationship with you.  You're special to me.<br>
<p>
Don't take things which don't belong to you.  Don't be greedy.  Work for what<br>
you need and *share* if your sister want's or needs the extra.  You do love<br>
your sister don't you?  Don't swipe away the opportunities for her to have a<br>
better life now and forever.<br>
<p>
Now one thing we don't tolerate in this house, is lying.  Tell the truth!<br>
If it hurts you, tell the truth!  Don't say things about each other <br>
which are not true.<br>
And if you don't know what the truth is, *find out*, before you make a mistake<br>
and paint a false picture.<br>
<p>
Don't lust for things which belong to your neighbor.  If you do, then <br>
you might<br>
want to take it away.  And I've already *told* you about stealing, <br>
killing, lying...<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
