[From Drew Corrigan]<br>
<p>
Hi All,<br>
<p>
A friend of mine received an item of unsolicited mail - apparently a part of<br>
a large "to the householder" mailing - the other day. This was a booklet<br>
which claims to be extracts from a book written over 100 years ago by <br>
E.B.White. The title is something like "Will America Survive" (though this<br>
is not the title of the original work). The full book is offered for $9<br>
and copies of this booklet for $2. A business called "Four winds Trades" is<br>
given as the place to order copies. What caught my friend's attention is<br>
that the booklet is right down the line with what the WCoG believes.<br>
<p>
Has anyone heard of or does anyone know anything about a "E.B.White"? (Not, <br>
Ellen G. White, but distinctly, E. B. White. - at least according to my <br>
friend.)<br>
<p>
Thanks,<br>
<p>
Drew.<br>
<p>
[E. B. White was an American author of children's books including <br>
'Charlotte's Web' and 'The Trumpet of the Swan'.  But somehow I doubt<br>
this would be the same E.B. White.  SCT]<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
