[From Tony Dyson]<br>
I'm with Beng on this one. I see the Branch Davidian shootout as another<br>
indictment against the way firearms seem to be so much a part of American<br>
society.<br>
<p>
A friend of mine was a student missionary in Thailand last year, and whilst<br>
there he met a few American sm's. He recounted to me their shock and <br>
disbelief that he had not only never fired a gun in his life, but that his<br>
lack of firearms did not worry him at all and that he didn't feel oppressed<br>
or insecure. <br>
<p>
I applaud the historic stand that America has taken for liberty and freedom<br>
of speech, thought and action. Looking at the results of &gt;200 years of<br>
"liberty", though, I question the way it has been implemented. Koresh has<br>
been quoted as criticizing the governments of Britain, Australia and other<br>
countries for depriving their citizens of firearms, which are necessary for<br>
self-defence. He sees this as oppression of the people. Well, due to my <br>
government's oppressive stance, I am unlikely to face the business end of a <br>
.50 calibre machine gun, licensed or unlicensed.<br>
<p>
The entire firearms debate leaves me slightly bemused, since I personally<br>
have never desired to own or fire one, and I see few legitimate uses for<br>
them in Western society. Obviously, though, there are other Christians<br>
who do feel differently, so it is unlikely that the Christian church will<br>
lead any disarmament crusade. Perhaps we'll have to leave that up to the<br>
new age movement!<br>
<p>
Anyway, the SDA church administration should be very careful what they<br>
publish regarding some of the other splinter groups and "independent<br>
organizations", just in case they are as well prepared for battle as the<br>
Branch Davidians!  ;-&gt;<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<p>
[I think this should be the last word on gun control for a while.  SCT]<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
