<title>Mar_1993: Discipleship or dispute?</title>
<h1>Discipleship or dispute?</h1>
<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i><br>
<i>08 Mar 1993 15:21:47 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#78">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#78">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#78">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#78">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0079.html">Harvey Brenneise: "E.B. White ??"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0077.html">Steven Timm: "Guns"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0083.html">Sherman Cox: "Re: Discipleship or dispute?"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Raylene and I try to visit other churches from time to time. The following<br>
is a "statement of mission" which appeared in a church bulletin.<br>
<p>
------<br>
                           ..... CHURCH<br>
<p>
                             STATEMENT<br>
                             =========<br>
<p>
OUR BUSINESS	Developing effective lives for God's glory <br>
		(Eph 4:11-16, Jh 10:10)<br>
<p>
OUR MISSION	The mission of ... Church is one of evangelising,<br>
		nurturing and developing people to a commitment to<br>
		Christ, Commitment to the body of Christ, and<br>
		Commitment to the work of Christ.<br>
<p>
OUR PRODUCT	Changed lives, ie fruitful and fulfilled people.<br>
<p>
THEOLOGICAL FOUNDATIONS<br>
<p>
	a)	A Great Commitment to the Great Commission and the<br>
		Great Commandment will develop a Great Christian<br>
		and grow a Great Church. (Mth 22:36-40, Mth 28:19-20)<br>
<p>
	b)	That Christianity is a lifestyle. (Jh 10:10)<br>
<p>
COMPONENTS<br>
	<br>
	1)	Every believer is a  MEMBER of Christ's family.	(Rm 12:5)<br>
	2)	Every believer needs MATURITY.			(Eph 4:13)<br>
	3)	Every believer is a  MINISTER.			(Eph 4:12)<br>
	4)	Every believer is a  MISSIONARY.		(Acts 1:8)<br>
<p>
OUR CUSTOMERS<br>
<p>
		The Community	- Uncommitted<br>
		The Crowd	- Those who just attend<br>
		The Congregation- Those committed to the Church Family<br>
		The Committed	- Those committed to maturity<br>
		The Core	- Those committed to ministry and mission<br>
<p>
OUR PROCESS<br>
<p>
	*	Attract the COMMUNITY's interest by meeting felt needs.<br>
	*	Introduce the CROWD to a relationship with Christ.<br>
	*	Incorporate believers into the CONGREGATION.<br>
	*	Ensure that all members feel loved, cared for and part<br>
		of the family.<br>
	*	Develop mature members to be COMMITTED to the habits of<br>
		spiritual growth.<br>
	*	Help people find a personal ministry and move into the<br>
		CORE.<br>
	*	Allow people to see their purpose in living through MISSION.<br>
<p>
-----------<br>
<p>
Isn't that a positive, constructive approach? I don't like being negative,<br>
but I sometimes get the feeling that we as SDAs are worrying far too much<br>
about "distinctives" and institutional survival that we are neglecting the<br>
basics of Christian living. Surely the most important principle of all<br>
is that of being Christ's disciple.<br>
<p>
We can either expend all our energy arguing over just what that means,<br>
or we can "just do it". In the words of a good friend of mine, God gave<br>
us so many good things, that if we spent more time chasing those we wouldn't<br>
have any time to worry about the things that aren't so good. <br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
