<title>Mar_1993: E.B. White ??</title>
<h1>E.B. White ??</h1>
Harvey Brenneise (<i>brneise@edmund.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 8 Mar 1993 10:40:08 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#79">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#79">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#79">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#79">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0080.html">davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com: "Maxwell's Letter"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0078.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Discipleship or dispute?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
As a reference librarian, it's always frustrating to try to answer a<br>
second or third hand reference question, as was the question about E.B.<br>
White.  The problem is that often a question needs to be corrected<br>
before it can be answered, and this is hard to do when you can't query<br>
the person with the most information.<br>
<p>
My first approach was to scan titles in OCLC, the huge database of over<br>
23 million bibliographic items that most libraries use to catalog books.<br>
I didn't find anything that fit (but then the question indicated that<br>
this might not be the correct title).  I also had no success with Books<br>
In Print, although I did find that Four Winds Press publishes a lot of<br>
children's books.  In searching OCLC I also found 98 titles published<br>
between 1839 and 1954 by anyone with the initials E. B. White.  Almost<br>
all of these were from the 20th century, and most were by the famous<br>
author of children's books and _The Elements of Style_ and _New Yorker_<br>
author.  Other interesting titles were _The Lady Is Cold_ and a 1929<br>
title, _Is Sex Necessary?_ (maybe they needed such a title that year!).<br>
Without further information I don't think I can accomplish much more in<br>
the national bibliographies (incidentally, I also checked the massive<br>
print _National Union Catalog_ but can't really search for initials and<br>
didn't want to check all of the authors with the last name of White and<br>
a first name beginning with E--although I did notice quite a few<br>
entries for an author whose first name was Ellen!).<br>
<p>
Harvey Brenneise<br>
Head Reference Librarian<br>
Andrews University<br>
Internet: brneise@andrews.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
