<title>Mar_1993: Branch Davidians</title>
<h1>Branch Davidians</h1>
<i>AAGAARD%morekypr.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu</i><br>
<i>06 Mar 1993 15:34:36 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#84">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#84">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#84">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#84">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0085.html">Woody Baker: "Re: Shootout in Texas"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0083.html">Sherman Cox: "Re: Discipleship or dispute?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0043.html">Fred Christiansen: "re: Branch Davidians"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Perhaps this information already made the net and I didn't see it --<br>
I seem to have missed some of the messages on this topic.  However, in<br>
case nobody has already mentioned it, this information on the Branch<br>
Davidian cult (like in Waco) came from someone interviewed on National<br>
Public Radio.  The Branch Davidians (BD) began to separate from the<br>
SDA church in Southern California in the late 1930s.  In 1942 they<br>
officially split off over the subject of pacificism -- the BD were<br>
completely pacifist at that time and the regular SDA church was not.<br>
Obviously something happened in the intervening years.  There are about<br>
1500 BDs in the US and about that many more elsewhere in the world.<br>
The 1500 US members are spread across about 7 congregations, one of<br>
which is in Waco, Texas.  Apparently none of the others is prone to<br>
stockpiling arms, and the Waco branch were influenced in that direction<br>
by their leader.  This is not the first time there has been shooting<br>
down there -- when we lived in Oklahoma there was a shootout between<br>
followers of two divergent prophets of the BD in Waco.  Nobody was<br>
killed, or even harmed seriously in that outbreak however.  This David<br>
Koresh guy had practiced his group in an endtime scenario when he<br>
believed the forces of the world would attack them because of their<br>
beliefs.  Obviously, when they were stormed by the agents it looked<br>
as though that time had arrived.<br>
<p>
Sorry if this was already well-known by everyone.<br>
<p>
Lola<br>
Aagaard@Morekypr<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
