Below is one of the newspaper report I found:<br>
<p>
The media in Hong Kong reported the shootout in detail.  The leader of the<br>
cult is David Koresh, 33, who previously went by the name Vernon Howell and<br>
is said to believe he is Jesus Christ.  His group is called "Branch<br>
Davidian".  Koresh told the CNN television network by telephone that he<br>
would release two children each time the radio station played the tape he<br>
dictated to federal agents.  The tape is about the group which believes in<br>
free love and that the end of the world is near.  4 FBIs and 2 of Koresh's<br>
followers were killed during the shootout.<br>
<p>
The group claimed that it was a branch of SDA but SDA declined to have any<br>
relations with this group.  "Branch Davidian" was founded in LA in 1933 and<br>
was actually separated from the SDA church at that time.  The founder was<br>
from Bulgaria and he believed Jesus would return in 1934.  After his death,<br>
his wife prophesized that Jesus would return on April 22, 1959.  Then the<br>
group was divided into two and "Group Dividian" was one of them.  Koresh<br>
started to lead the group in 1984.<br>
<p>
Looks like Koresh has nothing to do SDA.  It was the founder of the cult who<br>
was once an SDA.<br>
<p>
Hope this mail can give you some information about the cult.  There are<br>
plenty of information I found but that was written in Chinese.<br>
<p>
                                                  Asa<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
