Thanks for the doctrinal statement.<br>
I've perused it and find it quite interesting.<br>
In many regards, my beliefs are quite similar<br>
to those stated in this document.<br>
<p>
As you probably realize, the most "distinctive"<br>
distinctives in this document are those which<br>
are directly traced to Ellen G. White.  I have<br>
an honest question:  What relative weight is given<br>
the teachings of EGW which are not directly<br>
substantiated by the scriptures, compared to that<br>
which is clearly taught in the scriptures?  By <br>
and large, does the average man (or woman) in the<br>
SDA church place the same emphasis on the prophecies<br>
of Ellen White?  Is adherrence to her teaching a<br>
test of fellowship?<br>
<p>
Thanks for considering my questions.<br>
<p>
In Christ,<br>
Scott Hinks<br>
