<title>Mar_1993: news coverage of Waco, TX (San Jose and Japan)</title>
<h1>news coverage of Waco, TX (San Jose and Japan)</h1>
Danny Kumamoto (<i>kumamoto@sj.ate.slb.com</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 8 Mar 93 13:06:00 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#93">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#93">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#93">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#93">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0094.html">Wil Clarke: "Re: church in Texas"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0092.html">Trevor Tompkins: "Re: Thoughts on the Waco standoff"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
To SDAnet,<br>
<p>
For those who are curious:<br>
<p>
San Jose (California) Mercury News have printed articles and opinions<br>
on the Branch Davidians every single day since March 1.  It's been<br>
covered in the front pages (about five or six day for the past eight<br>
days) and in the religion section (this past Saturday), along with few<br>
opinion sections, including a letter to the editor by an SDA minister.<br>
Apart from the minister's remark, I only saw two references to SDA --<br>
once in the Mar 1's first page, and the other in the religion section.<br>
<p>
In Yomiuri Shinbun -- a Japanese daily newspaper -- there were only<br>
two articles on the Waco incident for the past week (up to Mar 7), and<br>
the only denomination mentioned was Seventh-day Baptists(!!) -- not<br>
once about SDA.  In fact, the two articles never made the front pages<br>
(things like bribery scandals and strong yen did).  The English<br>
version of Yomiuri Shinbun had two front page articles on it (Mar 2<br>
and 3), but they dealt only with the Branch Davidians.  Yomiuri<br>
America (published in Japanese, once a week, exclusively on American<br>
news -- this includes Canada and Latin America) was completely silent<br>
this past Friday about Waco.<br>
<p>
Danny<br>
<p>
Internet:  kumamoto@sj.ate.slb.com<br>
MaBellNet: +1 408-437-5154<br>
SLOWNET:   Schlumberger Technologies, ATE<br>
           1601 Technology Drive, San Jose, CA  95115, U.S.A.<br>
<p>
  "Where are the men?" the little prince [asked.] "It is a little<br>
lonely in the desert..."<br>
  "It is also lonely among men," the snake said.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
