<title>Mar_1993: Waco Rumors</title>
<h1>Waco Rumors</h1>
Stan Macasieb (<i>macasib@rtsg.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 9 Mar 1993 12:16:22 -0600</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#98">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#98">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#98">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#98">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0099.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Re: Pacifism"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0097.html">Russell Yonkers: "Pacifisim and the Church"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0292.html">DOWE001%TSU.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu: "Re: Waco Rumors"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
SDANetters:<br>
<p>
Help me either substantiate or dispell a rumor I've heard when I attended<br>
church last Sabbath. <br>
<p>
There was a report that, as an aftermath to the shootout, a number of<br>
residents burned down a SDA church in Waco. This particular member of<br>
the church also told me that the pastor here at North Shore Chicago<br>
knows about it, but won't say anything lest it caused an uproar.<br>
The pastor had his start as a student pastor in the Waco area, and<br>
is very familiar with the Branch Davidians' activities. <br>
<p>
Why was it not in the press, I asked the person. He said that, because<br>
the media is so hung up on the incident itself, they didn't take<br>
notice of the retributions going on.<br>
<p>
BTW, the president of the Illinois Conference sent to all comm secy's,<br>
including me, a copy of a press release re BD and its differences<br>
and history with the SDA church last Friday. I'd use it in my<br>
newsletter, but, by the time the April issue comes out, I'd hope the<br>
Waco incident would be resolved. At this rate, though, David Koresh<br>
may have more believers in his divinity outside of his compound. Sigh!<br>
<p>
--stan (macasib@degas.rtsg.mot.com)<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
