This is not at all a simple issue.<br>
<p>
Take a medic who repairs combat troops. Those troops whose lives have been<br>
saved then go back to fight some more. So the medic is doing just as much<br>
to aid the killing as "the clerk who types the order to kill" or the truck<br>
driver carting the ammunition.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
