<title>Mar_1993: Re:  Thoughts on the Waco standoff</title>
<h1>Re:  Thoughts on the Waco standoff</h1>
Woody Baker (<i>woody@knapper.cactus.org</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 09 Mar 1993 08:29:56 CST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#100">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#100">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#100">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#100">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0101.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "pacifist != won't fight"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0099.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Re: Pacifism"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0046.html">Steven Timm: "Thoughts on the Waco standoff"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
The local paper reported that most of the automatic weapons were purchased<br>
as normal semi-automatic weapons (example AR-15, which is the civilian semi<br>
auto only version of the M-16), and then were converted by the group to full<br>
auto.  The conversion for the AR-15 is fairly straight forward.  Replace the<br>
ar-15 bolt with an M16 bolt (legeal), replace the hammer with an M16 hammer<br>
(once again legal), replace the disconnector with an M16 selector lever<br>
(again legal), install the auto-sear. (Illegal without getting the BATF<br>
permit.)  Plans are available for manufacturing an auto-sear that drops in,<br>
requiring no modificaton to the reciever.  Now, it should be said that you<br>
CAN get in trouble for installing the bolt, hammer, disconnector and<br>
selector lever, but it is leagal to buy them.  The M-16 bolt is a better<br>
bolt.  However, it requires all parts to be truly functional.<br>
<p>
This conversion is strictly Illegal unless you have the permit, and go <br>
through the background check.  It seems that this is what the group did.<br>
No way to trace the weapon, simple to do (a file, drillpress, hacksaw and<br>
vice, and a level of knowlege that any high school student posses).<br>
<p>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
<pre>
-- 
Woody Baker Postscript consultant/Flint knapper  512-837-8317 (Austin, Tx)
<p>
"If you ain't bleedin' you ain't knappin'" ---&gt; go ahead, ask me...
<p>
woody@knapper.cactus.org
woody@chinacat.unicom.com (temporary) is forwareded to woody@knapper
</pre>
