<title>Mar_1993: pacifist != won't fight</title>
<h1>pacifist != won't fight</h1>
<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i><br>
<i>10 Mar 1993 09:13:23 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#101">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#101">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#101">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#101">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0102.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: Pacifisim and the Church (2 more anecdotes)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0100.html">Woody Baker: "Re:  Thoughts on the Waco standoff"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
----&gt;<br>
I have read the posts about pacifiscm with some amusment and also some<br>
aprehension.  The church that my wife and I attended when we became<br>
adventists was located outside of an Air Force base on which I was<br>
stationed.  They never mentioned the fact that the church took a <br>
pacifistic stance.  I subsequently heard about it after I left the<br>
Air force and resumed civilian life.  I was upset that people took<br>
such a strong stance on it and that I had never heard about it before<br>
I have since just let the issue drop but feel that either I was <br>
decieved by the church or there is a wide disparity in positions<br>
held on this issue.  <br>
&lt;----<br>
<p>
I can understand how you felt there, Russell. Perhaps your fellow<br>
church members didn't want you to feel that you didn't fit in as<br>
a part of the church group, and couldn't think of a non-critical<br>
way to tell you that they were not in favour of carrying arms. <br>
Besides, as you have suggested, I think there *is* a wide disparity<br>
in positions held on this and many other issues.<br>
<p>
----&gt;<br>
I worked with nuclear weapons and carried arms in the Air Force and <br>
would do it again today if I had it to do over again.  I would also<br>
support any one of my children entering the military if they so<br>
chose to do so in what ever capacity they would chose.  I feel strongly<br>
about my rights to bear arms and have recently been shopping for firearms.<br>
&lt;---- <br>
<p>
Surely a person can be anti-war and anti-violence and still bear arms<br>
in the military, just as one can be anti-abortion and still be pro-choice.<br>
I myself, were I to join the military, would not refuse to serve in a<br>
combatant role, although I doubt that I would relish the experience. (The<br>
real thing is a bit of a far cry from Falcon 3 and AOTP, which I do relish).<br>
<p>
At the same time, I was one of those who posted to the net regarding guns.<br>
In my *personal* opinion, a firearm is an item of hardware designed <br>
specifically to maim or kill another living creature, and I am opposed<br>
to their proliferation in society around me. I have friends who feel<br>
differently, and they are still my good friends. Besides, you have to<br>
understand that I have grown up outside the U.S., and I think that my<br>
attitude to various things reflects that.<br>
<p>
----&gt;<br>
I fear from the descusion that I read on SDAnet I fall despretly short<br>
on the christian lifestyle ladder because of my beliefs.  Is the church <br>
really such a strong "peace" church or is the tone of the conversation<br>
just much stronger then the actual beliefs?<br>
&lt;----<br>
<p>
I could be wrong, but I think most Christians are in favour of peace. But<br>
basic human rights is another thing we are all in favour of. Sometimes we<br>
have to choose between a set of poor options, and try to select the best<br>
one. Just as an example, I can cite the current situations in Iraq, Bosnia<br>
and Somalia. To be "pacificist" to the extent that others can be oppressed<br>
I believe to be wrong.<br>
<p>
The carrying of arms is an issue which you can argue about until the<br>
ethernet melts, but outside of a situation requiring an actual decision it<br>
is all fairly academic. As I said, I am strongly opposed to the proliferation<br>
of firearms in society, but were I to live in a place where my life was in<br>
danger, maybe I would own one myself, and learn how to use it. I don't know.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
