<title>Mar_1993: Re[2]: Thoughts on the Waco standoff</title>
<h1>Re[2]: Thoughts on the Waco standoff</h1>
Chad Peckham (<i>cpeckham@devmail.sps.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 10 Mar 93 08:39:44 CST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#109">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#109">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#109">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#109">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0110.html">davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com: "OLD/NEW COVENANT Compared"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0108.html">Steven Timm: "Text of hymns"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Being from Austin, Texas (right in the heart of the Texas Republic) our<br>
paper has followed this standoff daily. This last Sunday's paper had about<br>
75% of the first section dedicated to numerous articles about this. In<br>
fact, one page was dedicated to two articles about SDA beliefs. Quite well<br>
done, I thought.<br>
<p>
One article caught my attention regarding the weapons that Koresh has. It<br>
is legal to buy a 50m machine gun in Texas. A local gun store owner has<br>
one in his store. You do have to have a license though and approved by the<br>
BATF. It seems Koresh must have been getting his arsenal illegally. The<br>
tip off to the BATF that this arsenal existed was a UPS package that broke<br>
open upon delivery to the compound and revealed grenade casings. Seems<br>
there is an unscrupulous (sp?) weapons mail order firm in Florida under<br>
investigation.<br>
<p>
--Chad<br>
<p>
p.s. Glad to be back on the email list! Thanks, Steve.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
