<title>Mar_1993: OLD/NEW COVENANT Compared</title>
<h1>OLD/NEW COVENANT Compared</h1>
<i>davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com</i><br>
<i>Wed, 10 Mar 93 07:43:10 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#110">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#110">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#110">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#110">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0111.html">Russell Yonkers: "Des Ford writings"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0109.html">Chad Peckham: "Re[2]: Thoughts on the Waco standoff"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
The following is a chart I put together a couple of years ago for s.r.c.<br>
And I posted it to SDAnet.  This last weekend I attended a series of<br>
meetings by Larsen.  Excellent studies from the Bible and EGW.  One of<br>
his topics was a study from the Bible and EGW on how Jesus is the<br>
perfect and complete sacrificial atonement.  Also his perfect priestly<br>
atonement.  Before the cross there was the sacrifice of lambs and the<br>
mediatorial role of the priests, preceded by the Patriarchs.  After<br>
the cross we have the perfect "lamb" slain once as well as the perfect<br>
High Priestly work of Atonement of Jesus.  The point he was making is<br>
that we can accept the Calvinist position of Jesus dying a perfect and<br>
complete sacrificial death of Atonement, replacing the death of lambs<br>
slain from the foundation of the world.  But we also believe in the<br>
perfect work of priestly atonement that Jesus serves in the heavenly<br>
temple built without human hands.  While Jesus death was a perfect<br>
and complete work of sacrificial atonement, we also believe in His work<br>
of priestly Atonement which replaces that of the Old Covenent priests.<br>
<p>
So, I came home and fired up my MAC and researched the texts to incorporate<br>
into my chart.  So, here is an update:<br>
<p>
                                     =======================================<br>
WHAT DID NOT CHANGE                  |   OLD COVENANT   |   NEW COVENANT   |<br>
============================================================================<br>
<i>| For all who obey Him               | Deut. 7:9        | Heb 5:9          |</i><br>
+------------------------------------+------------------+------------------+<br>
<i>| Also for strangers, Gentiles,      | Lev 24:22        | Gal 3:28,29      |</i><br>
<i>|    and the "nations"               | Isa 42:6; 45:22  |                  |</i><br>
<i>|                                    | Ps 67:1-7; 22:27,28                 |</i><br>
+------------------------------------+------------------+------------------+<br>
<i>|God does not change                 |Deut 4:2          |Matt 5:17-20;     |</i><br>
<i>|God's law does not change           |Psalm 111:7,8     |Luke 16:17        |</i><br>
<i>|                                    |Eccl 3:14         |Heb 1:12; 13:8    |</i><br>
<i>|                                    |Isa42:21          |James 1:17;       |</i><br>
<i>|                                    |Dan 7:25          |1 John 2:7-11     |</i><br>
<i>|                                    |Hab 3:6; Mal 3:6  |1 John 1:5,6      |</i><br>
+------------------------------------+------------------+------------------+<br>
<i>| Love your neighbor as yourself     | Lev 19:18        | Matt 22:39       |</i><br>
<i>|                                    |                  | Mark 12:33       |</i><br>
+------------------------------------+------------------+------------------+<br>
<i>| With all your heart, soul and might| Deu 6:5; 10:12,13| Mat 22:37        |</i><br>
<i>|                                    | Deut 11:13; 30:6 | Mark 11:30       |</i><br>
<i>|                                    | 2 Kings 23:3     | Luke 10:27       |</i><br>
+------------------------------------+------------------+------------------+<br>
<i>| Law to be placed in the heart      | Deut 6:5,6       | Jer 31:31-33     |</i><br>
<i>|                                    | Ps 40:8          | Heb 8:10         |</i><br>
<i>|                                    | Prov 3:1         | Rom. 2:14-16     |</i><br>
+------------------------------------+------------------+------------------+<br>
<i>| Circumcision of the Heart          | Deut 30:6        | Rom 2:28,29      |</i><br>
+------------------------------------+------------------+------------------+<br>
<i>| Forgive and remember sins no more  |2 Ch 7:14 Ps 86:5 | Jer 31:34        |</i><br>
<i>|                                    | Ez 18:21-24, 31  | Heb 8:12         |</i><br>
<i>|                                    | Ez 33:11-16      | 1 John 2:1-4     |</i><br>
============================================================================<br>
