<title>Mar_1993: Reformers and the Antichrist</title>
<h1>Reformers and the Antichrist</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 12 Mar 1993 10:25:00 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#115">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#115">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#115">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#115">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0116.html">Steven Timm: "Advice for a culturally deprived SDA"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0114.html">Malachi Robertson: "Donahue and Waco stuff"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0122.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re:  Reformers and the Antichrist"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In the ongoing discussions on the CHRISTIA list, Ruben Gonzalez<br>
(who has been a big help on our side) has brought up the point that<br>
what SDA's say about the Catholic church is no different than what<br>
the various reformers have said, and brought out a various list<br>
of reformers who referred to the pope as Antichrist, including Luther,<br>
Wesley, and others.  <br>
<p>
I have heard this many times, but don't know where to find the reference<br>
on such.  Can anyone help?<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
