<title>Mar_1993: Advice for a culturally deprived SDA</title>
<h1>Advice for a culturally deprived SDA</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 12 Mar 1993 10:57:23 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#116">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#116">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#116">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#116">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0117.html">Steven Timm: "Unclean meats and Genesis 9"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0115.html">Steven Timm: "Reformers and the Antichrist"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0154.html">Woody Baker: "Re: Advice for a culturally deprived SDA"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Having been brought up in the flatlands of Michigan, where we were brought<br>
up to learn that wearing a wedding band was a Sin Against the LORD,<br>
and ran several people out of church for that reason, I was deprived of <br>
the Sabbath School lesson that tells one how to wear a wedding ring.<br>
I find myself rather lost interpreting the present situation, because<br>
I never learned how and where a wedding ring was supposed to be worn.<br>
Not that I plan to wear one myself anytime soon, but since I went <br>
through the SDA colonies while the "watch code" was still sort of in effect,<br>
I need to interpret the new "ring" code.<br>
<p>
Which hand is a wedding ring supposed to be worn on?  What about these <br>
people who have an extra ring with some translucent rock attached?<br>
What about people who have rings on all their fingers--what does that mean?<br>
And why does the ring seem to be declining in culture at large as a symbol <br>
of marriage just as it is making its ascendancy in SDA-land?  Is <br>
this another example of the older generation permitting what they were not<br>
allowed as young people?  Or is it the case, like jazz music, where<br>
the cultural connotations are different now than when it first came out<br>
so now it can be permitted?<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
