<title>Mar_1993: Re: Unclean meats and Genesis 9</title>
<h1>Re: Unclean meats and Genesis 9</h1>
Sherman Cox (<i>scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 12 Mar 93 12:13:28 CST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#120">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#120">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#120">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#120">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0121.html">davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com: "Re: Unclean meats and Genesis 9"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0119.html">Michael Merginio: "Re: Donahue and Waco stuff"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0117.html">Steven Timm: "Unclean meats and Genesis 9"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0121.html">davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com: "Re: Unclean meats and Genesis 9"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Steve Timm Writes<br>
<i>&gt; The Adventist view on clean and unclean meats points back to Genesis 7</i><br>
<i>&gt; to show that the regulations of clean and unclean were known to Noah and </i><br>
<i>&gt; thus predate Sinai.  But in Genesis 9, where God gives Noah instruction</i><br>
<i>&gt; in diet, we read in vs 3, 4  "Every moving thing that is alive shall </i><br>
<i>&gt; be food for you;  I give all to you, as I gave the green plant.</i><br>
<i>&gt; Only you shall not eat flesh with its life, that is, its blood."</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; In light of this, how is our doctrine defensible.  I'm not trying to tear</i><br>
<i>&gt; down our doctrine, I want to know the answer.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<p>
I was reading in Joe Crews book, "Answers to difficult bible texts."  The<br>
title is something like that, I cannot remember exactly.  He    answers<br>
this by keying in on the phrase ""as I gave the green plant."  He says<br>
that there are poisonus plants that God did not give to man so when God<br>
said I give you the green plant, He was talking about the "good" green<br>
plants, or those plants that were good for food.  Then the corelation is made<br>
to meats.  I beleive he talked about roaches and rats and how God does not<br>
want us to eat these things because they are detrimental.<br>
<p>
It all depends on your view of our keeping the health laws.  Are we doing<br>
it to be healthy, or are we doing it to follow some law.  Some say we are<br>
doing it to be healthy and yet we eat many things that are detrimental to<br>
our body.  Really to not eat unclean meats should of necessity cause us to <br>
eat correctly, because our reason is to be healthy.  Therefore, we should<br>
be exercizing, if we are refraining from unclean meats to be healthy.<br>
<p>
If we are refraining from unclean meats just to follow a law, we do not<br>
need to worry about such things as exercizing or eating healthier.  If<br>
we do this, however, I believe we miss the whole idea of the Health <br>
Message.<br>
<p>
<pre>
--
<p>
"All things are possible to him that believeth."
<p>
Sherman H. Cox, II       scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu
</pre>
