Steve,<br>
<p>
I don't have any info for you, but I'd like to say this.<br>
<p>
PLEASE don't belittle the significance of Christ's life, and principles.<br>
What I mean is this.  Limiting "Anti-CHRISTlikeness" to a single person<br>
or political/religious/social office does disservice to the significanc<br>
of what Christ exemplified in his life.  It also gets us into lots of<br>
unnecessary trouble, in name calling.  Sure, point out how the papal<br>
system is against the very foundations of Christ's character, and<br>
principles, but don't fail to give an equally passionate argument for,<br>
all other things which are "anti-CHRIST-like."<br>
<p>
marcuss@microsoft.com<br>
