<title>Mar_1993: David Koresch</title>
<h1>David Koresch</h1>
Russel Maxwell (<i>GR9032%SIUCVMB.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>05 Mar 1993 17:57:22 -0800</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#147">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#147">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#147">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#147">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0148.html">AAGAARD%morekypr.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu: "Ford's address"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0146.html">David Plaisted: "meats"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
the leader of the cult in TX, was a Seventh-Day Adventist until i believe 1987<br>
 when he was disfellowshipped.  I heard an Adventist on CNN talking about the<br>
situation.  He was an extreme radical and basically got kicked out of the<br>
church.<br>
<p>
That is not my concern.  My concern is this.  If we are to take the bible and<br>
the spirit of Prophecy seriously, then we know that things like in Waco TX<br>
will happen to US, the ones who are standing for truth.  I do not see David K<br>
as anything other than an enemy of GOD,  God did not ask us to hoard up weapons<br>
, but it places a stigma against Adventist's as a whole.<br>
<p>
but in the future, we will be called the radical ones, accused of terrible<br>
crimes against God and man.  What will we do when we see our fellow Christians<br>
and friends acused of terrible things. And listen to horrible claims on CNN,<br>
about YOU and ME.<br>
<p>
And what does this say about GOD?  when people say, "Why should I listen to you<br>
, you people are connected to that Cult in Texas."  How can I as a Christian<br>
continue.  this type of thing i believe, will be the thing that will lead many<br>
out of the church.<br>
<p>
think about this.  THE ONLY PRESS THAT THE SEVENTH-DAY ADVENTIST CHURCH HAS<br>
RECEIVED IN THE RECENT PAST HAS BEEN A CONNECTION TO A CULT WHERE CULT MEMBERS<br>
WERE KILLING GOVERNMENT AGENTS.  This is NOT good.<br>
<p>
To me this should serve as a call to arms, so to speak, to show the world the<br>
wonderful things about the God we serve. and the beauty of the Advent Message.<br>
<p>
thanks for putting up with my rambling.<br>
<p>
Russel Maxwell<br>
GR9032@SIUCVMB.BITNET<br>
GR9032@SIUCVMB.SIU.EDU<br>
<p>
I welcome any comments and communications.  thanks.<br>
