Election day in the United States is always on a Tuesday, but in the <br>
Presidential nominating process the primary elections and caucuses are <br>
on different days.  The Michigan caucus has been on Saturday for the<br>
last few elections.  As a result I was not able to participate when I lived<br>
there.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
