<title>Mar_1993: SDAs and the military</title>
<h1>SDAs and the military</h1>
<i>AAGAARD%morekypr.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu</i><br>
<i>12 Mar 1993 13:28:44 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#158">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#158">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#158">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#158">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0159.html">Steven Timm: "Archive available of recent CHRISTIA discussion"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0157.html">Maurice George Ashton: "Re Australian Elections"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Re: enlisting in the military, nobody has brought up the issue of the<br>
cost of our schools!  I know many premed and predental students who<br>
prayerfully considered all possible options for paying for their<br>
postgraduate training at Loma Linda and finally joined the military<br>
in order to get through medical or dental school.  Some just served<br>
their required time, but others have pretty much made the military a<br>
career.  If Adventism is upset by its members being career "warriors"<br>
then we should do something to make it more affordable to go to school<br>
without the help of the government.<br>
<p>
Lola<br>
Aagaard@Morekypr<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
