<!-- body="start" -->
The recent discussion on wedding rings reminded me that the<br>
question of jewellery had to be resolved in our own house in the<br>
last twelve months. My daughter brought home a boyfriend who<br>
wears two earings in one ear. He is also kind, thoughtful<br>
studious, respectful to us, respects my daughter, goes to church,<br>
takes part in services etc. Somehow a couple of bits of wire in the ear<br>
no longer seem all that significant anymore.<br>
<p>
Maurice Ashton<br>
Avondale College<br>
