<title>Mar_1993: Re: Relevance of Prophecy</title>
<h1>Re: Relevance of Prophecy</h1>
Russell Grau (<i>reg@ctshp.celtech.com</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 15 Mar 1993 12:00:19 -0800</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#168">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#168">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#168">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#168">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0169.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Reformers and the Antichrist"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0167.html">Alvin Vitangcol: "Regarding the CHRISTIA archive..."</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0129.html">Tim Swensen: "Relevance of Prophecy"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Tim Swensen asks regarding --&gt;&gt; Subject: Relevance of Prophecy<br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;I would appreciate it if some of you folks would answer these questions.  I</i><br>
<i>&gt;am formulating a sermon on the topic "The Relevance of Prophecy" and would </i><br>
<i>&gt;like to gauge the importance of prophecy to contemporary Seventh-day </i><br>
<i>&gt;Adventists.</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;Questions:</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;  To what degree is a correct understanding of Biblical prophecy important to</i><br>
<i>&gt;  your daily experience as a Seventh-day Adventist Christian? </i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<p>
Without a correct understanding of Biblical Prophecy, you have a LARGE void in<br>
the belief system of Adventism.  It is this prophetic base that leads many to <br>
understand why Adventists are so special (not all, but many).  This also implies<br>
that many already know the Lord and just are having further truth unfolded to<br>
them.<br>
<p>
If you want to see what a correct version of the truth will give you, just look<br>
at the rest of the evangelical world.  They do NOT have a correct understanding<br>
and are "blown about by every wind of doctrine."  I have watched my in-laws over<br>
the last few years.  They are pentecostal believers.  They started out with an<br>
overwhelming belief in the writings of various conservative "prophets" or such.<br>
<p>
Since the fall of Communist Russia, there has been a backpedeling in their <br>
knowledge.  There is a search for commonality.  A desire to "offend no one" no<br>
matter what.  Doctrine is no longer important in their belief systems.  There<br>
is a great break down in what makes them "different" from other beliefs or even<br>
other sects of Christianity.<br>
<p>
Our message of the certainty of prophecy has been the backbone of our beliefs.<br>
<p>
Without this certainty, there would be NO SDA's today.  Why?  Because 1844 would<br>
not have occured.  There would have been no study by William Miller.  There <br>
would have been no real urge to study the prophecies.  Of course, we know that<br>
God's hand is in this and that is WHY the study actually went forward and to<br>
the conclusion that it did.<br>
<p>
We also have the continuation of the prophecies that are leading us forward to<br>
that great and glorious day.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;  What about prophecy makes it this important?</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
Prophecy is a direct revelation of God.  It is the one thing that I can point to<br>
today and say, "See, here is where God has lead in the past.  Because of this I<br>
can trust God to lead me in the future."  Without prophecy I have no idea where<br>
we would be today.<br>
<p>
I can tell you, that without prophecy:<br>
<p>
	- the Hebrews would not have been looking for a redeemer from Egypt<br>
	- the wise men would not have been looking for the Messiah<br>
	- Abraham would not have looked for a son<br>
	- Adam would have died without hope<br>
	- David would never have been king<br>
<p>
Prophecy is sure.  It is the future revealed Word of God to us.  It gives me<br>
hope, looking at how God has dealt with us in the past, that He will do the same<br>
for us in the future.  It lets me know that Jesus is coming again.  It tells me<br>
that while the future may be filled with sorrow, Jesus is the Overcomer and the<br>
matter is sure.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;You relatively brief answers would be very much appreciated.</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
Hard to be brief about such a wonderfully important subject.<br>
<p>
Yours in Christ,<br>
<p>
Russell<br>
<p>
