<title>Mar_1993: Are you trustworthy?</title>
<h1>Are you trustworthy?</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 16 Mar 1993 21:16:08 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#177">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#177">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#177">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#177">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0178.html">Rich Hannon: "biographical info"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0176.html">Ben Clausen: "Re: new subscriber"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0190.html">Cam Litvin: "Re: Are you trustworthy?"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I am looking for a trustworthy person with the time and the inclination to <br>
do me a small favour.<br>
<p>
[For non-IBM PC types, a GUS is a Gravis Ultra Sound board, the premier<br>
sound board for the PC.  SCT]<br>
I am interested in purchasing a GUS, and I'm wanting to compare the price<br>
here in Australia with the cost of getting one shipped out from the US.<br>
Is there anybody on SDAnet who might be willing to (a) inform me what<br>
the current going price is over there, and (b) buy one and ship it out<br>
to me if it turns out to be worthwhile?<br>
<p>
I know this request is not really a part of the "charter" of SDAnet, but<br>
I'm hoping it gets through because I would be a little nervous about<br>
sending x hundred dollars to just anyone.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
[Watch out for import duties, and if you would put it in writing for a<br>
non-SDA, do it for a net member as well.  SCT]<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
