<title>Mar_1993: "anti" posts on christia</title>
<h1>"anti" posts on christia</h1>
<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i><br>
<i>16 Mar 1993 16:45:25 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#180">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#180">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#180">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#180">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0181.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Not a pacifist?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0179.html">CHRMD@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Re: Donahue"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0195.html">Woody Baker: "Re: "anti" posts on christia"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I find it interesting that most of the "anti" stuff on christia has <br>
been posted by an ex-SDA. It actually sounds like the same guy that<br>
appeared on Donahue, although the fact that both are blind doesn't<br>
necessarily mean anything. So the point is that most of his feelings<br>
regarding EGW are probably based on his experiences as an SDA.<br>
<p>
Whatever else may or may not be true regarding EGW, I'm convinced that<br>
her writings have been criminally used and abused by SDAs. Some of it<br>
has been honest mistakes made by well-meaning people, but probably some<br>
of it also by those wishing to add "authority" to their own personal<br>
hobbyhorse. The lady must turn in her grave sometimes.<br>
<p>
 From what I've read, she was actually quite a lovely person, quite the<br>
opposite of what guys like Dan seem to think. Blaming Spectrum, Walter Rea<br>
and Ronald Numbers for the problem isn't really fair either. You won't<br>
hear many Spectrum writers "using EGW as a club". Mostly they seem to<br>
be trying to paint a *more* reasonable portrait of EGW than what has<br>
sometimes been portrayed. As for Rea and Numbers, or Rea at least, they<br>
may be a bit like Dan - just reacting to an unfortunate misuse of EGWs<br>
role and her writings.<br>
<p>
I sometimes wonder whether the way the misuse of EGW has caused some to<br>
stumble relates at all to the text about the millstone around a person's<br>
neck. Gruesome, I know, but it's in the Bible!<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
