<title>Mar_1993: Re: "anti" posts on christia</title>
<h1>Re: "anti" posts on christia</h1>
Woody Baker (<i>woody@knapper.cactus.org</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 17 Mar 1993 08:59:14 CST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#195">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#195">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#195">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#195">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0196.html">Steven Timm: "Re:  The nature of Christ"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0194.html">Jeff Gates: "Arch of Noah +"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0180.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: ""anti" posts on christia"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I am formulating a reply to several of the points that were brought up<br>
in the post of the excerpts from CHRISTIA or whatever.  I feel obliged to<br>
point out that Ellen White never ever considered herself a prophetess or a<br>
prophet.  She explicitly went out of her way to make that known in several<br>
places in her writings.  Neither does she have the same relation to the <br>
Adventist church, as say Mary B. Eddy does to the church that she founded.<br>
The Seventh-day Adventist church CAN stand alone on the bible, with or without<br>
Ellen White in the picture.  Sola Scriptura...  My personal feeling is that<br>
we should recognize that we feel that EGW provided guidance that was inspired<br>
to the church in it's formative years.  She also brought to gether much<br>
contemporary material and integrated it.  Once again, we believe under God's<br>
guidance.  I personlly feel that we should drop the swearing of allegence<br>
to the inspration of Ellen White that is contained in the baptisimal vows<br>
that are taken by a new member.  I'm not avocating abandoning EGW, but rather<br>
feeling that our church can stand alone on the bible.<br>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
<pre>
-- 
Woody Baker Postscript consultant/Flint knapper  512-837-8317 (Austin, Tx)
<p>
"If you ain't bleedin' you ain't knappin'" ---&gt; go ahead, ask me...
<p>
woody@knapper.cactus.org
woody@chinacat.unicom.com (temporary) is forwareded to woody@knapper
</pre>
