<!-- body="start" -->
I wonder if there is any official church policy that states that <br>
the conference officers must be ordained?  There's at least one <br>
department director at the GC (Shirley Burton) who is not.  One bit of<br>
SDA history that we tend to forget that the first president of the first <br>
conference that was organized  (Michigan) was William S. Higley, a layman.<br>
We are also seeing in some conferences a trend away from ordaining the<br>
treasurers who have not had previous ministerial experience.  The<br>
decoupling<br>
of ordination from high church office is one of the goals which must be<br>
accomplished if we are to progress towards the equality of women in <br>
the SDA church.<br>
<p>
Unfortunately, the trend is much more likely to be to bestow an honorary<br>
degree in accounting on whatever minister is named the treasurer,<br>
than vice versa.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
