I must admit that such posts make me a bit hot under the collar.  Soon I<br>
relax though :) I was wondering if any comments were made in regards to<br>
the scapegoat doctrine?  In looking at the Sanctuary service and in<br>
looking at some of the NT texts that tie Jesus in with the Sanctuary<br>
service I find the Adventist view further confirmed in my mind.  To me the<br>
evangelical view leaves certain items unexplained that Adventist<br>
interpretation does not.  In a related note I found it interesting that in<br>
my historical-criticism slanted OT theology class here at Iowa it was<br>
pointed out that the scapegoat is in context being sent to some "demon"<br>
thing.  It wasn't quite what I believe but it came close.  My only mental<br>
difficulty of late is trying to see how this scapegoat view (where Satan<br>
gets to bear the sins of the cleansed) fits with the notion of Jesus<br>
taking the wrath of God upon Himself.<br>
<p>
Ian.<br>
