I was at the last General Conference Session and visited a booth that was<br>
set up to promote some of this alleged discoveries.  I saw photos of some<br>
wild stuff (giant jawbones?).  I also purchased what was supposedly a<br>
first among many books discussing these discoveries.  This was on Noah's<br>
Ark.  He did provide some information about his work in there and<br>
referenced some other fellow who had more detailed information.  I also<br>
got a sheet that had his phone number on it.  I called it once to see if<br>
he had completed any more books.  A female answered and told me no.  I<br>
did, however, see a revamped copy of the book I had at an ABC bookmobile. <br>
When at the GC I did here a little more about the Ark of the Covenant<br>
business.  I heard the story of how he came about finding it through a<br>
small series of miracles.  I can't say whether he has really discovered<br>
all that he says that he has, but the book does point out that the Turkish<br>
government recognized him as the discoverer of Noah's Ark and was working<br>
on a tourist center before making a big deal of it.  The only problem here<br>
is that supposedly this was to be done a while ago, and I haven't heard<br>
anything about it.  I have heard that in a related matter that there was a<br>
CBS special on Noah's Ark and some Christians have been claiming that the<br>
Ark is found.  Does anyone know more about this recent matter?  Was<br>
Wyatt's name mentioned in it?  I am also supposed to be getting the name<br>
of some Texan who claims he has some evidence on the Ark.  On an<br>
interesting endnote:  the claim that the Ark was found was brought up on<br>
my local BBS and one users replied that even if a world wide flood was<br>
proved would that prove that what the Bible has to say is truth?<br>
<p>
Ian.<br>
<p>
<p>
[Allen Roy, a former SDAnet subscriber, was up on these things, and posted<br>
an article about Wyatt.  Roy is a ark-hunter himself, but believed that <br>
Wyatts claims were bogus.  I will try to dig out the article.  I heard <br>
part of Wyatt's talk myself at one point, but not enough to judge.<br>
There was a CBS news special years and years ago, saying nothing about<br>
Wyatt.  I don't know if there has been another one since on that topic.  SCT]<br>
