To Net:<br>
<p>
Sorry to mess up your definition on earrings and gays. But, the street talk <br>
in D. C. and Baltimore is that the definition that you all indicated is <br>
pase. Earrings in the right ear do not mean anything anymore. What Woody <br>
suggested was correct at one time but not any more.  At least around here <br>
back east!<br>
<p>
I suppose Gays may wear earrings in their right ear -- maybe more than one <br>
but it does not necessarily mean that they are gay.<br>
<p>
THOUGHT FOR TODAY:<br>
<p>
"A synonym is a word used in place of one you can't spell!"<br>
                                            ------Stokes<br>
