<!-- body="start" -->
Gentry's interpretation of radiohalos (although it is wrong) is not <br>
what troubles me.  In his book Creation's Tiny Mystery he goes farther in <br>
an appendix to attack the theory of special relativity, and proposes<br>
several schemes which violate Maxwell's equations just for starters. <br>
Even this wouldn't be so bad, except that several years ago he did the<br>
campmeeting tour and claimed scientific authority for saying this was <br>
invalid, confusing many SDA believers and building an artificial mistrust<br>
of physicists in the community.  I wrote to him about the obvious violations<br>
of physical law in this section of his book.  He responded but did not <br>
attempt to answer my question.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
