<!-- body="start" -->
Ever since there have been conferences (early 1860's) all church <br>
properties and school properties have been held in the name of the<br>
conference association.  It has happened several times that<br>
congregations who wanted<br>
to leave the denomination found themselves searching for a new church <br>
home because the conference came to reposess the building.  Woody<br>
suggested this was a power grab, but in fact the church has always had<br>
this power.<br>
<p>
It sounds, however, that the rule as was posted here is aimed at hospitals,<br>
these being the church institutions that would most likely be subject<br>
to control from outsiders otherwise.<br>
<p>
Please don't bring SDAnet into the context of this discussion.  SDAnet<br>
is not crazy enough to be institutionalized yet!  It's hard enough to<br>
face the <br>
task of becoming an organization with a real charter and a board of<br>
directors.   I have no desire to be listed in the Seventh-day Adventist<br>
Yearbook.  <br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
