<title>Mar_1993: Noah's Ark</title>
<h1>Noah's Ark</h1>
<i>ben@orion.lasierra.edu</i><br>
<i>Fri, 19 Mar 1993 09:46:14 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#223">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#223">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#223">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#223">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0224.html">Woody Baker: "Re: In the presence of alcohol consumption"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0222.html">Malachi Robertson: "Scapegoat"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
At the 1990 General Conference in Indianapolis, Indiana, Ron Wyatt had a booth<br>
located in a nearby hotel. It included a replica of the ark. At that time he<br>
believed that he had found: <br>
<p>
--- Noah's ark and 15 anchor stones<br>
--- the real Mt. Sinai<br>
--- Ammonites (giants) burial ground<br>
--- Moabite burial ground<br>
--- ark of the covenant and crucifixion site (crucifixion site directly <br>
above the chamber where the mercy seat of the ark of the covenant located)<br>
--- area where Moses struck the rock<br>
--- place where Korah and followers were swallowed up<br>
--- Aaron's grave<br>
<p>
The Institute for Creation Research (ICR) in San Diego has commented on Ron<br>
Wyatt's claims about Noah's ark in a 4 page Impact article of September 1992 by<br>
John D. Morris, Ph.D. This is a monthly publication that is sent out with their<br>
Acts &amp; Facts. Note that ICR is a conservative creation group that believes the<br>
entire universe is on the order of 6000 years old. John Morris has gone on ark<br>
hunting expeditions himself. He goes into the details of why Wyatt's claims<br>
cannot be substantiated. <br>
<p>
A conservative creation research group in Australia puts out a magazine,<br>
Creation Ex Nihilo. In the Sept-Nov 1992 issue (v.14, n.4), Andrew Snelling has<br>
a 13 page article, Amazing 'Ark' Expose. He goes through Wyatt's claims and<br>
states that they are all false: <br>
---radar shows man-made (boat) structures<br>
---there is a regular metallic pattern<br>
---lab tests show petrified laminated wood<br>
---Turkish scientists found metal rods<br>
---metal artefacts have been proved by lab<br>
---there are `ship's ribs' showing<br>
---there is lots of petrified wood<br>
---Turkish Commission says`it's a boat'<br>
<p>
I'd be willing to comment more if someone is interested, or send copies of<br>
these articles.<br>
<p>
	Ben Clausen<br>
	Geoscience Research Institute<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
