WELL... many of the parties we have at work, have some kind of alcohol <br>
involved.<br>
I personally get tired of it, and have avoided some socials because of <br>
it.  I had a<br>
nice time at our Christmas bash, even though many people got sloshed.  <br>
One thing<br>
which angered me was getting served a soda out of a crude soda can, <br>
while alcohol<br>
drinkers received their alcoholic drinks were bottled in classy, <br>
festive bottles.<br>
I did more than get angry, I brought my concern to the catering <br>
committee, which<br>
decided to do quite differenly for next year's.<br>
<p>
Recently, some friends and I have decided to hold alcohol/drug/smoke-free home<br>
parties, as an alternative to the bars and clubs which attract many <br>
young people.<br>
<p>
marcuss<br>
