<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0227.html">Kwong-hoon Andrew Park: "Ruben, Tony Great job!!"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
My theory is that there is a finite percentage of the entire population<br>
which is gullible in the way that Steve referred to, but that those people<br>
are attracted to the SDA church by some of our doctrines. Our prophetic<br>
interpretation (the certainty of it at least) and "remnant theology" are<br>
two examples. Hence the SDA church ends up with a higher percentage of<br>
those people than the general population.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
