<title>Mar_1993: Noah's ark</title>
<h1>Noah's ark</h1>
Nancy Vyhmeister (<i>vyhmeist@edmund.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 19 Mar 1993 09:14:58 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#233">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#233">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#233">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#233">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0234.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re:  Lord's Supper"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0232.html">TANG BENG YONG: "scapegotes"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Not being a specialist, I have no right to give a verdict on whether Noah's<br>
ark or the ark of the covenant have been found.  Siegfried Horn, well-known<br>
SDA archaeologist and Bible scholar, affirms that neither finding is genuine.<br>
By the way, this weekend the Horn Archaeological Museum at Andrews University<br>
is celebrating 25 years of archaeological expeditions and Dr. Horn's 85th<br>
birthday.   <br>
<p>
Nancy<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
