Hello people,<br>
	seeing the posts about Australian elections is quite interesting.<br>
Here in Singapore, we have had general elections on Saturdays the last two<br>
times i think, i can't remember before that. Anyway, voting was always<br>
a whole-day affair, so as the day they use is different from the biblical<br>
day, we SDAs could go to vote (voting is compulsory) after sundown when it<br>
was still saturday but Sabbath was over.<br>
	Hey, do any of you Australians know a Trudie Anne Desirens? She is<br>
now my cousin-in-law and is Mrs. Trudie A. Chew. She was from Australia<br>
before she came to live here in singapore. Or do any of you know Pastor<br>
Ken Martin? He was my church pastor for a while here.<br>
<p>
	- Beng.<br>
