<title>Mar_1993: Lord's Supper</title>
<h1>Lord's Supper</h1>
Gilbert Bailey (<i>gilbertb@lsid.hp.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 19 Mar 93 6:41:09 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#248">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#248">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#248">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#248">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0249.html">Bruce Holm: "Re: Things"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0247.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Christ's humanity"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0234.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re:  Lord's Supper"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
SDAnet,<br>
<p>
What follows are a number of questions regarding the celebration of<br>
the 'Lord's Supper' or Communion practices in the SDA Church.  The reason<br>
for this post is that our new pastor suggested, at our last church board<br>
meeting, that there isn't any scriptural evidence for excluding <br>
un-baptized children from participating fully in the service.  While I'm<br>
studing out this issue, I thought I'd post some of the questions raised<br>
and seek others opinions.<br>
<p>
Where young children allowed to participate in the Passover?<br>
<p>
If yes, and the 'Lords Supper' is the anti-type of the Passover for<br>
Christians, then shouldn't young children participate?<br>
<p>
Did Jesus celebrate the Passover with Joseph and Mary before He turned<br>
twelve and went to Jerusalem?<br>
<p>
If we hold a 'open communion' and allow other non-members to participate,<br>
why exclude our children?<br>
<p>
I know it depends upon the child, but how old does one have to be<br>
before he or she can love Jesus and wait for His return?<br>
<p>
As I grew up in the church I was told that I must wait to be baptized<br>
in order to 'fully understand' the significance of the bread and wine<br>
before participating.  What is the relationship between Baptism and<br>
the 'Lord's Supper'?<br>
<p>
Well, I'll stop now with the above list.  I'm sure all of you can think<br>
of more questions/answers.  Just as a side note, my 5yr old son, asks <br>
deeper questions than some 'mature' Christians, and based upon his later<br>
comments he has a rather firm grasp on principles involved after I've explained<br>
an answer(s) to his question(s).  He also seems to put into practice the things<br>
he learns much more readily than his 'more mature' counterparts.<br>
<p>
<pre>
--
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
| Gilbert Bailey, N7WVH                  (206) 335-2290 TELNET 335-2290      |
| Hewlett Packard Company                UNIX: gilbertb@hplsla.lsid.hp.com   |
| Lake Stevens Instrument Div., 8600 Soper Hill Rd., Everett, WA 98205-1298  |
