Hi there Tim<br>
<p>
Wow - that was quick - of course the time difference is just right now - I'm<br>
on my way home, and you have just come in - i suppose!<br>
<p>
Yes - please put me on the net - It looks good.  I'm all for using new<br>
technology for spreading the message within and without.<br>
<p>
Feel free to e-mail on any other query about this side of the world - and<br>
even just a personal Hi.<br>
<p>
About HBC and e-mail.  It's just a question of Beurocracy I think.  I have<br>
organized with our DP manager that they can link up with a phone link (typically daily)<br>
if they supply a modem here - and there of course.  But money is rather tight<br>
and the brethren probably have not seen the power of e-mail etc yet.  I think<br>
I will have to organize a demo and get the bug to byte.  I'll have to<br>
get you on the other side for a skeduled connection to really impress them!<br>
But today's turnover time is difficult to beat - and that not arranged!<br>
<p>
Well all the best - and God bless in your NET work there.  As I say, I'll be<br>
more than delighted to subscribe.<br>
<p>
Yes, NAC is a cyclotron with a small vd Graaff at FAURE near Somerset West.<br>
I'm situated at the vd Graaff, mostly using it as an analysis tool - I'm<br>
in solid state - spicifically silicides and related matters.  I spent some<br>
years lecturing after leaving Helderberg, but am in full time research at the<br>
moment.  I see you are also in Physics - it would be nice to chat about <br>
that sometimes too.  We might be able to link up some time in the future, as I<br>
should be going on a Post-doc in a year or so.<br>
<p>
God Bless<br>
<p>
Cecil<br>
