Hi There<br>
<p>
In the recent NAAP I find some college addresses.  That's good news.  You<br>
also have this mail address listed for more information about overseas<br>
colleges.  Well - I would like all the info you can give me - and in return<br>
I can give a little bit!<br>
<p>
I am at a research institution (similar to the Loma Linda Proton facility)<br>
near to Helderberg College in South Africa.  Even though I am not currently<br>
directly connected to HBC lecture-wise - I have a lot of friends there and<br>
have regular contact with them there.  A few guys and I are working on<br>
getting HBC up on the e-mail network via my work here, but that seems to be<br>
quite a way in the future - unfortunately!<br>
<p>
But as for now - I would be happy to pass on mail (within reason naturally)<br>
for guys there.<br>
<p>
You might mention this fact in your information on overseas colleges.<br>
<p>
I am actually trying to contact a few guys over there - but am a bit lazy to<br>
write - and too poor to phone for their e-mail addresses.  You wouldn't<br>
maybe have the addresses of the following:<br>
<p>
Dr A.O. Coetzee - Andrews<br>
Dr K.E. Thomas - Andrews<br>
Dr Will Clarke - La Sierra (if I remember correctly)<br>
Mr Gary Foster - Loma Linda<br>
<p>
It's nothing serious, or else I would have written naturally, but I would<br>
like to be able to contact them periodically via e-mail.<br>
<p>
I hope I hav'nt given you too much work!<br>
<p>
Maranatha<br>
<p>
Cecil Churms<br>
<p>
P.S.  Andrews doen't maybe have an anonymous FTP database of SDA-type stuff,<br>
like EGW on disk etc?  If it doesn't - it might be a good idea!  If it does,<br>
I would love to support it!<br>
<p>
Regards<br>
<p>
Cecil<br>
<p>
PPS.  I just remembered - I didn't ask for an address of some Physics guys at<br>
Andrews.  Any addresses available - I would like to contact them on a more<br>
professional level!<br>
<p>
Thanks<br>
