<title>Mar_1993: Mark Finley in Chicago Suburbs</title>
<h1>Mark Finley in Chicago Suburbs</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 23 Mar 1993 22:06:46 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#261">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#261">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#261">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#261">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0262.html">Cynthia Helms: "job announcement"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0260.html">Steven Timm: "151st member joins SDAnet today"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0264.html">P. Virgo: "Re: Mark Finley in Chicago Suburbs"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Mark Finley, SDA evangelist and speaker for the It Is Written television <br>
broadcast, has been here in the west suburbs of Chicago giving a series<br>
of meetings.  This is one of the first times that I have seen an SDA<br>
evangelist give first and only priority to presenting "Jesus Christ<br>
and him crucified."  It's called the Discover Jesus seminar, five nights<br>
of two 45-minute lessons apiece.  He begins with evidence for the historical<br>
Jesus and the historicity of the Bible, moves to the basics of salvation<br>
and a relationship of Christ, then moves to the certainty and nature<br>
of the Christ who is coming again.  This set of meetings will be followed<br>
by a more extended set by the local pastors.<br>
<p>
They've rented a 600-seat meeting hall with overflow space of 300, <br>
and it has been full for the first three of the five nights.  Videos of <br>
this seminar will be available in May.  It is coordinated with a set of <br>
It Is Written television programs that have been airing over the past <br>
couple months.<br>
<p>
It's also interesting to hear his story of preaching the gospel inside<br>
what had been the congress hall of the Kremlin.  Evidently an It Is Written<br>
team is now on its way to Moscow and in a short time there will be a <br>
set of meetings in the Olympic Stadium of Moscow.  They expect to seat 20000<br>
using half of the stadium and have two sessions each day.  Obviously they<br>
can use our prayers right now.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
