<title>Mar_1993: job announcement</title>
<h1>job announcement</h1>
Cynthia Helms (<i>helmsc@susan.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 24 Mar 1993 18:18:29 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#262">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#262">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#262">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#262">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0263.html">Sherman Cox: "Maxwell"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0261.html">Steven Timm: "Mark Finley in Chicago Suburbs"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
March 24, 1993<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
Please post the following job announcement to SDAnet.<br>
<p>
---------------------------------------------------------<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
March 16, 1993<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
Dear Colleague:<br>
<p>
Andrews University is seeking applicants to<br>
fill the position of Director of the James<br>
White Library, available July 1, 1993.<br>
Enclosed you will find a job announcement.  We<br>
invite you to apply for this position or share<br>
this information with interested candidates.  <br>
<p>
Located in the heart of the fruit belt of<br>
southwestern Michigan, the University is near<br>
many educational, cultural, and business<br>
institutions, as well as recreational<br>
facilities.  Andrews University is a center of<br>
Seventh-day Adventist higher education with<br>
students from nearly 80 countries.  Doctoral<br>
degrees are granted in theology and education.<br>
Numerous graduate and undergraduate programs<br>
are offered.<br>
<p>
Please respond to this opportunity for a<br>
challenging career in the denomination's<br>
largest academic library by April 15, 1993.<br>
<p>
Sincerely yours,<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
Cynthia Helms, Chair<br>
Search Committee<br>
James White Library<br>
(616) 471-6260<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
                            ANDREWS UNIVERSITY<br>
                            JAMES WHITE LIBRARY<br>
                             LIBRARY DIRECTOR<br>
<p>
<p>
The University and the Library<br>
<p>
     Andrews University is a Seventh-day Adventist university<br>
     located in southwestern Michigan, 100 miles east of Chicago. <br>
     The university consists of five schools offering degrees at<br>
     the doctoral, masters, baccalaureate, and associate levels,<br>
     with a student population of approximately 2,500 FTE drawn<br>
     from 80 countries of the world.<br>
 <br>
     The James White Library has total holdings of 1.2 million<br>
     items and 3,000 current periodical subscriptions.  There are<br>
     two branch libraries (Architecture and Music) and several<br>
     special collections (i.e., Media and Adventist Heritage).  The<br>
     library is in the process of implementing an Innovative<br>
     Interfaces automated integrated system.<br>
<p>
     The library staff includes 12 professional librarians, 20<br>
     staff members, and 80 student workers.  The library is a<br>
     member of several local and national consortia and <br>
     participates in regional resource sharing.  The library<br>
     operates on an annual budget of $2 million.<br>
<p>
Responsibilities of the Position<br>
<p>
     --Develop policies and long-range plans for the library.<br>
     --Introduce and support appropriate new technology.<br>
     --Provide dynamic leadership.<br>
     --Oversee the various services of the library.<br>
     --Prepare and implement the budget.<br>
     --Communicate the needs of the library to appropriate groups.<br>
     --Function as personnel director for the library.<br>
     --Serve on various on-campus and off-campus committees.<br>
     --Report to the Associate Vice President for Academic       <br>
       Administration.<br>
     <br>
Qualifications<br>
<p>
     --M.L.S. from an A.L.A. accredited library school.<br>
     --Second master's degree or earned doctorate preferred.<br>
     --Progressive library administrative experience.<br>
     --Strong communication and interpersonal skills.<br>
     --Creative leadership and managerial skills.<br>
     --Experience with current library trends such as        <br>
       internationalization and emerging technology.<br>
     --Seventh-day Adventist in good and regular standing.<br>
<br>
Salary and Benefits<br>
<p>
     --Minimum salary, $34,000.<br>
     --Faculty rank.<br>
     --12-month plan with vacations and holidays according to <br>
       policy.<br>
     --Medical, dental, and retirement benefits, plus tuition     <br>
       assistance.<br>
<p>
Application Procedure<br>
<p>
     --Send letter of application, resume, and at least three <br>
       letters of recommendation to Cynthia Helms, Chair, Search<br>
       Committee, James White Library, Andrews University,<br>
       Berrien Springs, MI 49104-1400.<br>
     --Applications should be received by April 15, 1993 to ensure<br>
       consideration.<br>
       <br>
       <br>
