<title>Mar_1993: Re: Mark Finley in Chicago Suburbs</title>
<h1>Re: Mark Finley in Chicago Suburbs</h1>
P. Virgo (<i>virgo@metter.fmpmis.metter.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 24 Mar 93 15:37:12 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#264">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#264">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#264">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#264">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0265.html">Sherman Cox: "Spectrum"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0263.html">Sherman Cox: "Maxwell"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0261.html">Steven Timm: "Mark Finley in Chicago Suburbs"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Mark Finley, SDA evangelist and speaker for the It Is Written television </i><br>
<i>&gt; broadcast, has been here in the west suburbs of Chicago giving a series</i><br>
<i>&gt; of meetings.  This is one of the first times that I have seen an SDA</i><br>
<i>&gt; evangelist give first and only priority to presenting "Jesus Christ</i><br>
<i>&gt; and him crucified."  It's called the Discover Jesus seminar, five nights</i><br>
<i>&gt; of two 45-minute lessons apiece.  He begins with evidence for the historical</i><br>
<i>&gt; Jesus and the historicity of the Bible, moves to the basics of salvation</i><br>
<i>&gt; and a relationship of Christ, then moves to the certainty and nature</i><br>
<i>&gt; of the Christ who is coming again.  This set of meetings will be followed</i><br>
<i>&gt; by a more extended set by the local pastors.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; They've rented a 600-seat meeting hall with overflow space of 300, </i><br>
<i>&gt; and it has been full for the first three of the five nights.  Videos of </i><br>
<i>&gt; this seminar will be available in May.  It is coordinated with a set of </i><br>
<i>&gt; It Is Written television programs that have been airing over the past </i><br>
<i>&gt; couple months.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; It's also interesting to hear his story of preaching the gospel inside</i><br>
<i>&gt; what had been the congress hall of the Kremlin.  Evidently an It Is Written</i><br>
<i>&gt; team is now on its way to Moscow and in a short time there will be a </i><br>
<i>&gt; set of meetings in the Olympic Stadium of Moscow.  They expect to seat 20000</i><br>
<i>&gt; using half of the stadium and have two sessions each day.  Obviously they</i><br>
<i>&gt; can use our prayers right now.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Steve Timm</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<p>
It's great to hear such things. I'll have to say special prayers for<br>
Mark Finley and all who are out there trying to spread the message!<br>
In times like these, people need to know that there is Someone out<br>
there who knows they're hurting and is waiting to release them from<br>
their pain and love them.<br>
<p>
Paul E. Virgo<br>
