<title>Mar_1993: LSU presidential search</title>
<h1>LSU presidential search</h1>
Bill Allen (<i>allen@polaris.lasierra.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 25 Mar 1993 08:45:18 -0700 (PDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#275">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#275">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#275">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#275">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0276.html">Steve Hix: "Re: Gentry's halos"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0274.html">Kwong-hoon Andrew Park: "Re: Gentry's halos"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
The search for a new president for La Sierra University started with the<br>
announcement in September by president Fritz Guy that he would end his term of<br>
service at the end of this school year.  The search committee chaired by<br>
trustee Jerry Wiley (faculty/administration of the USC law school), got off<br>
to a slow start and has clothed their activities in secrecy. Wiley has been<br>
said to have the committee on a short leash and a muzzle.  LSU provost,<br>
Garland Dulan has been removed from the committee for giving general and vague<br>
information to the campus about the work of the committee.  The secrecy<br>
makes the following information all the more interesting.<br>
<p>
Authoritative information coming from off campus indicates that the leading<br>
candidates for the position are the presidents of AUC, PUC, and WWC<br>
(Gerity, Maxwell and Andreasen).  The information has further interest in<br>
that the three appear to have been selected before Wiley sent letters<br>
asking the fifty-one individuals nominated by the university faculty and<br>
administration if they would consider the position.  Gerity is now said to be<br>
coming to the campus for interviews this coming week.<br>
<p>
Stay tuned.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
