<title>Mar_1993: Adventist Beliefs</title>
<h1>Adventist Beliefs</h1>
Sherman Cox (<i>scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 25 Mar 93 7:59:27 CST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#278">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#278">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#278">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#278">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0279.html">David Plaisted: "Toads"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0277.html">Sherman Cox: "Maxwell"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
When I was in denominational Jr. Academies I learned many things.<br>
One of the things that stuck with me was an acronym to remember some of the<br>
beliefs of the Adventist Church.  I learned this at Cedarvale Jr. Academy in<br>
Raytown MO  The Acronym was BROTHER and 8 S-es:<br>
<p>
Baptism by Immersion<br>
Religious Liberty<br>
Ordanances - Lords Supper, <br>
Tithe and Offerings<br>
Health and Temperance<br>
End of the Wicked<br>
Rightousness by Faith<br>
<p>
Sin<br>
Second Coming<br>
Sabbath<br>
Sanctuary<br>
State of the Dead<br>
Satan<br>
Spirit of Prophecy<br>
<p>
I forget the other S.<br>
<pre>
-- 
<p>
"All things are possible to him that believeth."
<p>
Sherman H. Cox, II       scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu
</pre>
