Since we're discussing science in this group, I'd like to make a<br>
different kind of comment.  According to Science Magazine, toads<br>
and frogs seem to be disappearing all over the world, for some<br>
unknown reason.  However, this isn't true in North Carolina.<br>
Two days ago, my children came home with a plastic container full<br>
of over 90 toads, chirping loudly away.  Yesterday they caught<br>
215 of them.  (All but a few were quickly repatriated.)  When<br>
you see a boy with 90 toads you know that the Lord has a sense<br>
of humor.<br>
<p>
	Dave Plaisted<br>
