----&gt; <br>
 He talked about the magazine Spectrum.  I have heard of it, but he talked of <br>
 that magazine writing the view that the beasts were social ills and that<br>
 the remnant were social activists.  Does anyone know about this.  I have<br>
 never subscribed to the magazine.  Does it routinely print such things that <br>
 are so far out of adventist thought?<br>
&lt;----<br>
<p>
I haven't read Spectrum much either, and haven't come across the ideas<br>
mentioned here. But I would like to point out that the authors who submit<br>
material to Spectrum are indeed Adventists, so it is incorrect to say that<br>
those views are far out of Adventist thought. Besides, how can a person<br>
develop in their ideas if they never entertain new ones? Is the printing<br>
of a new idea equivalent to endorsing that idea as undisputed truth?<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
