Following on what Steve had to say.<br>
<p>
A big plus I find in SDAnet is that we talk about issues and get<br>
away with it.  If a Sabbath School class at my church was to say<br>
the same things, by way of discussions, as are discussed on SDAnet, <br>
there would be some serious rumblings coming down from church<br>
leadership.  I am a conservative in a conservative SS class in a<br>
largely liberal church.  Our SS leader has to be careful to steer<br>
the class away from certain discussions and back to the lesson<br>
outline and even then he gets invited in for confrontations with<br>
the SS committee and/or the church pastors.  To openly discuss<br>
some of what I have posted would have shut down our class a long<br>
time ago.<br>
<p>
And so I appreciate the forum of SDAnet.<br>
<p>
DaveB<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
