During the war my home church also had lengthy prayers, services, etc. concernin<br>
   g the war.  I was relieved though that a number of people made clear that sid<br>
   e<br>
taking was not the issue and shouldn't be the issue in war time, but the issue<br>
should be that the destruction ends as swiftly as possible, for wars are<br>
battles of principalities and powers between good and evil and not between men.<br>
God is the author and basis of life and peace, not confusion and destruction<br>
that as is often associated with war.<br>
Also, several Sabbaths, information was passed on concerning the church in<br>
Baghdad.  Word had reached the US for the NAD churches to pray for their<br>
welfare, if I'm not correct, they fared miracously well.<br>
<p>
Lawrence J. Dowe<br>
