<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0290.html">Steven Timm: "Info (fwd)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
The idea of tagging all SDA subject lines with SDA: has been mentioned<br>
before.  On the surface it's a good idea, but<br>
<p>
1)  Not everyone will do it, therefore<br>
2)   I would have to add it<br>
3)   That's a royal pain.<br>
<p>
Sorry!<br>
<p>
<p>
Those on Unix machines who find this a problem, I would suggest<br>
investigating the Elm mailer.  This can automatically sort SDAnet<br>
messages from other <br>
messages.  If you have elm at your site, I can send you a set of filter <br>
rules that will do that.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
