<title>Mar_1993: Is bunching working OK?</title>
<h1>Is bunching working OK?</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 26 Mar 1993 17:59:01 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#293">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#293">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#293">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#293">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0294.html">Sherman Cox: "Adventist Believe"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0292.html">DOWE001%TSU.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu: "Re: Waco Rumors"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
You should have noticed that over the past week, the messages have been<br>
sent out in a single bunch each day.  Every day except today that was<br>
in the evening Central Standard Time, which means the Australians can get a<br>
fast reply in while I am still posting.  The dual goal was to slow down <br>
traffic somewhat and to keep at least most of the readership from having mail<br>
hitting their terminal during work hours.  Also;, it saves me some time.<br>
Sometimes I lose track of what messages have been sent out already, though,<br>
and as a result send them out twice.<br>
<p>
Let us know what else can be done to improve service.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
