<title>Mar_1993: Why the SDA church needs conservatives</title>
<h1>Why the SDA church needs conservatives</h1>
Paul Gates (<i>70516.420@compuserve.com</i>)<br>
<i>26 Mar 93 23:51:35 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#302">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#302">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#302">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#302">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0303.html">Woody Baker: "Re: Gentry's halos"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0301.html">Paul Gates: "Adventist thought &amp; Spectrum"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Steve, I wonder if we have a clear cut definition of liberals at least? The <br>
founders of our country were considered liberal because they wanted <br>
freedoms for everyone. I think that the ones who are called liberals today <br>
(outside of the church that it), are more like socialists because they want <br>
to take away from some to give to others. <br>
<p>
I perceived  that Short, Wieland, etc were the liberals trying to get at <br>
the truth of 1888. The Conservatives I thought were the ones who were <br>
saying, we always have practiced Right. by faith and there never was a <br>
rejection of the message in 1888.<br>
<p>
I do not mean to be nitpicking!! That is just my perception. Of course <br>
Labels can be confusing some of the time!<br>
<p>
I gave Gary Russell your Internet address and he will probably joining one <br>
of these days. I was thinking he may wait till after he is moved to Calif. <br>
in June.<br>
<p>
...........Paul<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
