<!-- body="start" -->
Steve Timm:<br>
<p>
Steve, I have been using a baptismal form to prepare for baptism that I got <br>
from Jay Gallimore in Mich when he was v. Pres. It is called the summary of <br>
our beliefs. I quote:<br>
<p>
"The gifts of the Holy Spirit are given to the body of Christ as he <br>
chooses. They are given to enable the Christian and the church, to become <br>
effective wintesses for Jesus. The gift of prophecy, one of the most <br>
desirable gifts is one of the identifying marks of the remnant church. <br>
Seventh-day Adventists recognize that this gift was manifested in the life <br>
and ministry of Ellen G. White."  In this statement are a lot texts for <br>
support but I have left them out for brevity on the net. This essentially <br>
is what is found in the church manual because the above was adapted from <br>
the SDA church manual by the Northwest Ministries Training Center of the N. <br>
Pacific Union Conf.<br>
<p>
The Baptismal vows that you mention I go over with the candidate previous <br>
to the day of baptism. In the church service I usually mentioned those <br>
being baptized have been properly instructed in the teachings of our church <br>
etc.<br>
<p>
............Paul<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
