<title>May_1993: 100 Years of Education in South Africa</title>
<h1>100 Years of Education in South Africa</h1>
<i>CHURMS@nacdh4.nac.ac.za</i><br>
<i>17 May 1993 11:58:28 +0200</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#109">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#109">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#109">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#109">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0110.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Promises for Sabbath Problems"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0108.html">Steven Timm: "female homosexuality in the bible?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
We are celebrating 100 years of Adventist Education in South Africa this year.<br>
One of the main events is a "home-coming" week-end at Helderberg College <br>
from 20 May to 23 May.<br>
<p>
I'm sure some of you out there have had connections with Helderberg, or know of<br>
someone who has.<br>
<p>
In a similar way in which it is customary to send telegrams of congratulations<br>
I wonder if any of you would like to send a message to Adventists in general<br>
and Helderberg in particular over this weekend.<br>
<p>
I have arranged that I will pass on any such mail to the organisers of the<br>
weekend - and also to the alumni supper (Thursday night) where applicable.<br>
<p>
Anyone interested?<br>
<p>
Maranatha<br>
<p>
Cecil Churms<br>
(Mail me direct if you wish at CHURMS@NACDH4.NAC.AC.ZA)<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
