<!-- body="start" -->
I think we need to remember that the issue of News is not only a matter<br>
of principal.  It is a matter of cost to the organization giving access<br>
to news.  The question then also becomes:  should an SDA school be<br>
paying money in order to give students access to materials which are<br>
definitely against the principles of the institution?<br>
<p>
 From a stewardship standpoint, I do not believe that we should fund<br>
activities which go contrary to our principles.  If students wish to<br>
access the information, that is their choice, but let them do it<br>
at their own expense.<br>
<p>
Ron<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
