Lola asked about Mark Martin and the tapes she had received.<br>
<p>
I remember Mark when he was at Pacific Union College in the late 70's. I had <br>
several classes with him. I believe, Lola, you were there at the time so you <br>
might look him up in an old "Funny Book."<br>
<p>
As I remember him he was very nice but totally consumed by 1888. At the time <br>
there were several who were deeply interested in 1888, but I think Mark had <br>
his own interpretation of what happened.<br>
<p>
As to how he got your address, there are many ways ministries get lists. Many <br>
purchase lists from other sources, in some cases Unions have sold their <br>
mailing lists although I don't know of any who do that any more. I know of at <br>
least one independent ministry who paid someone to steal a mailing list.<br>
<p>
Maybe this info is too old now but I don't always get to my Compuserve account<br>
on time these days.<br>
<p>
Ed Fargusson (Compuserve 72450,2430)<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
