<!-- body="start" -->
Just a few comments -- one of our church officials said that Adventist<br>
pastors were aware of some objectionable material in NLP.  One<br>
person here rewrote the program to remove this.  Even after this,<br>
some pastors were uncomfortable with it and more was removed.<br>
So it's not just the rumor mongers that were concerned.<br>
<p>
It didn't help that books like ``Frogs to Princes'' and<br>
``Trance-Formation'' were on the recommended reading list even<br>
for Lab I.  Also, I was told by a conference official that<br>
since Lab I  and II were used, LEAD consultants have gone into<br>
hypnotism and don't see anything wrong with it, so the churcch<br>
has stopped using their stuff.<br>
<p>
Any corrections to this info would be appreciated.  But I didn't<br>
get most of it from the independent ministries.<br>
<p>
	Dave Plaisted<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
