<!-- body="start" -->
Whilst reading in Churchhill's History of the English Speaking People,<br>
Intro to Vol 1, he refers to the "Pelagian heresy" re free-will (no<br>
specifics).  From an ardent Protestant stand-point (vs his CofE (?)),<br>
I'm curious if maybe it wasn't so heretical after all.<br>
<p>
Can someone outline for a simple plough-boy (to borrow Wycliffe (?))<br>
what this was about?  Thx.<br>
