<!-- body="start" -->
Dear SDAnetters:<br>
I have mixed feelings about announcing that the text of David Koresh's<br>
radio address back in March is available via anonymous ftp.  But, I think<br>
there may be some who have an interest in reading and studying the<br>
erroneous teachings that led over 70 men, women, and children to a fiery<br>
death at Ranch Apocalypse.   This is especially intriguing to us in view<br>
of the fact that the majority of those who perished in the flames had at<br>
one time been members in good standing of the SDA church.  What happened<br>
to them?  What did the Davidians offer that we didn't? Could their<br>
departure from our church have been avoided by more love and support from<br>
our members?  Do we just write them off as "weak members" who were led<br>
astray, or did Christ say we are to protect the weak members?  These are<br>
very interesting questions....<br>
<p>
To obtain the rather lengthy text of Koresh's speech, ftp to 130.43.3.3<br>
and go to the following directory: /Library/Religion/Fringe .  The name of<br>
the file is "koresh.txt" and it's in regular ASCII.<br>
<p>
I'd be interested to hear any feedback from the net on the questions I've<br>
raised above and/or on the text of Koresh's speech.<br>
<p>
NOE@TENET.EDU<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
