First off, the news about the young people's BASIS, and predominate focus of<br>
faith is extremely good news!  We should rejoice.  I'd agree with Tang.<br>
More and more young people in the church view the law of God (in context of<br>
the principles which make His character and kingdom) as complimentary to<br>
their belief in salvation by grace through faith.  You see the fruit of <br>
it in their<br>
speaking out *against* inconsistencies and non-Christ-like ways perpetrated in<br>
the name of "morality", religion and tradition many times rooted deeply <br>
in "church<br>
culture".  Not unlike what Christ did while on earth.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
