I notice that it's been over a year since I first joined SDAnet and<br>
put out my bio info.  I hope it not untoward to re-introduce myself<br>
since the list has gone from 100 to 200+ in the meantime.  If memory<br>
serves, Steve did this recently also.  So ...<br>
<p>
Geographic bio:  Born in Fredericton, NB, 1953; Bangalore &amp; Madras, India,<br>
1956-62; Andrews U area, 62-63; Calcutta, India, 63-66; Simpsonville, MD,<br>
66-67; Oshawa, ON, 67-71; Sarnia, ON, 71-75 (schooling at AU &amp; Collonges);<br>
Lukanga, Zaire, 75-77; Waterloo, ON, 77-79; suburbs Minneapolis, MN, 79-82;<br>
suburbs Phoenix, AZ, 82-88; suburbs Portland, OR, 88-91; Phoenix thereafter.<br>
<p>
Education bio:  Home schooled grades 1-3,5,6; Vincent Hill School, India;<br>
Atholton Jr Acad (Md); Kingsway Academy; Andrews U; Univ of Waterloo.<br>
<p>
Work bio:  Trans-Africa Div of SDA, Zaire; Honeywell, MN; Motorola, AZ;<br>
BiiN &amp; Intel &amp; Portland State U, OR; Motorola again (OSI comm software).<br>
<p>
Family bio:  Parents, Grace &amp; Gerhard Christiansen, Willowdale, ON; sister<br>
Linda Flowers, South River, ON; married wife Kathie Ewald in 1975; children<br>
are Liesl (almost 16, Weimar Academy, home schooled before that), Monique<br>
(12, home school), Andrew (5), Bonnie (2).<br>
<p>
Service bio:  SS teacher in CR, Kg, Pri, Jr/Teen, Youth; deacon, elder; some<br>
lay preaching; sign interpreting for the deaf in Tempe, AZ, and Gladstone, OR.<br>
<p>
Spiritual challenges:  2nd child becoming profoundly deaf at age 6 months, 1981;<br>
laid off from Honeywell, 1982;  3rd child born premature, 10 weeks in NICU,<br>
1988; employer BiiN collapsing, 1989; 1st child collapsing during camp-out,<br>
near coma (ketosis, ketoacidosis), due to undiagnosed type 1 diabetes, 1992.<br>
<p>
"It will be worth it all, when we see Jesus.<br>
 Life's trials will seem so small, when we see Christ.<br>
 One glimpse of His dear face, all sorrow will erase,<br>
 So bravely run the race, 'til we see Christ."<br>
