<title>May_1993: Des Ford and firm no</title>
<h1>Des Ford and firm no</h1>
<i>AAGAARD%morekypr.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu</i><br>
<i>05 May 1993 18:57:04 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#44">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#44">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#44">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#44">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0045.html">Steven Timm: "Possible new services of SDAnet"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0043.html">Fred Christiansen: "What was the Pelagian "heresy"?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Well, mention Des Ford and you _knew_ you would hear from me, didn't<br>
you?  Culturally, Des Ford is more of an Adventist than I am!  He<br>
repudiated a couple of doctrinal positions that he considered non-<br>
salvific issues, but he is still a big upholder of the general culture<br>
and lifestyle of adventism.  I may be telling you something that you<br>
already know, Steve, but your post sounded as though you were throwing<br>
Ford in with the liverated lifestyle crowd, and he definitely is a<br>
conservative in that area.  (<br>
(That was supposed to be "liberated" two lines up there!)<br>
<p>
Lola<br>
Aagaard@Morekypr<br>
