Hello people,<br>
	does anyone know anything about a guy called John Ellis or something<br>
like that, who has been advertising in some newspapers, including the one at<br>
Waco, and putting in a long article with strange claims in it? Apparently he<br>
claims to be the pastor of a 1 member SDA church, and calls the branch<br>
Davidians the "matyrs of the Mount Carmel SDA church" and claims that there<br>
are 10 million SDAs in the world, of which 3 million are not under the GC,<br>
and seem to form some sort of stricter sect of SDAs (they are all<br>
vegetarians, presumably of the vegan type, and the men wear suspenders<br>
instead of belts and the ladies long flowing skirts, don't own TVs etc) and<br>
then goes on to make other strange claims, even quoting E G White in the<br>
process. He end with a call to action against the rich merchants or<br>
something like that, which sounds like communist ideology.<br>
	Anyway, if non-SDAs read this guy's ads, they might think his views<br>
are representative of our, and that would be a misrepresentation indeed.<br>
<p>
-beng<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
