<title>May_1993: May 3 and Portland, OR</title>
<h1>May 3 and Portland, OR</h1>
Bruce Holm (<i>bruceh@wv.mentorg.com</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 6 May 93 10:00:09 -0700</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#42">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#42">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#42">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#42">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0043.html">Fred Christiansen: "What was the Pelagian "heresy"?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0041.html">Fred Christiansen: "(Re) Introducing myself to SDAnetters"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Hello fellow netters,<br>
<p>
I posted a message about a week ago about a John Gunter (an evangelical from an<br>
Assemblies of God church) predicting the end of Portland, Oregon due to an<br>
earthquake as part of God's judgement over the evil and satanic activity going<br>
on.  He got quite abit of media coverage on TV and radio with his street<br>
preaching techniques and caused quite a bussle of activity in the area.<br>
<p>
Well, as a follow-up, I guess you can see there are no news reports of such an<br>
event.  But I wanted to tell you that last night on our local (Portland) news,<br>
John (who had gone to Montana to ride out the destruction) publically admitted<br>
that his message was NOT from God and that this in no way negates the fact that<br>
a God in heaven does indeed exist.  He apologized to all for the inconvenience<br>
and hassle he caused people.  He is back to work here in the Portland area.<br>
<p>
So much for false impressions.<br>
<p>
--Bruce<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
