I think that the church is partly responsible for some of its<br>
serious members being drawn off into Waco type things.  People<br>
are hungry for some serious prophetic exposition which isn't<br>
found in the church today as much as it used to be.  They are<br>
also sensitive to our failures to live up to the light we have<br>
been given.  So it's easy for someone else to claim he has the<br>
true church which is more faithful than we are.<br>
<p>
	Dave Plaisted<br>
