<!-- body="start" -->
This is a rally sponsored by the "Twentysomething" group of Hinsdale, IL.<br>
Our guest speaker will be Ray Tetz, the associate director of Adventist <br>
Development and Relief Association.  Drama and musical presentations will <br>
be given in addition to the talks.  This will be held Friday night May 14 and<br>
Sabbath May 15 in Hinsdale, IL, in an office building on Salt Creek Lane.<br>
E-mail me for more details.  This promises to be really good.  If you <br>
are out of town accomodations can be arranged with local group members.<br>
(This means you, all the folks at Urbana-Champaign, Purdue, IU, etc.)<br>
<p>
I was totally awestruck to see the large list of names on the mailing <br>
list of people I know from college who I did not know were even in the area.<br>
We have some work to do hereabouts.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
