<title>May_1993: Ee's poetry</title>
<h1>Ee's poetry</h1>
TANG BENG YONG (<i>med10014@nusunix2.nus.sg</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 10 May 93 02:22:24 +0800</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#49">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#49">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#49">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#49">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0050.html">Steven Timm: "SDA-L: The SDA-L link to SDAnet"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0048.html">davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com: "Re: Waco"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Hello friends,<br>
	The following are some of the poems written by Ee Teck Ee, which i<br>
have collected from the back of church bulletins and the like. Just thought<br>
you might like to have a look through them.<br>
<p>
-beng<br>
<p>
<p>
    YOUR HANDS<br>
<p>
It was not always through green pastures<br>
That you made me lie,<br>
Nor always was i able to rest<br>
With still waters beside,<br>
Often with fear and copious tears<br>
I walked through fire,<br>
Then,<br>
With drooping head and misty eyes<br>
I cried, "O God, why?"<br>
Heaven was silent.<br>
The mystery deepened<br>
There was no reply<br>
But i felt a tightening grip:<br>
It was your hands on mine.<br>
The hands which were once pierced with nails<br>
And they pulled mine<br>
To touch your wounded side,<br>
Thus,<br>
Assured of your love<br>
I gained courage to journey on.<br>
I shall speak of your love far and wide<br>
And so hasten the day<br>
When in Heaven with you, all of us shall abide<br>
And when with the same hands<br>
You shall wipe all tears dry.<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
    MY MOTHER (from a child)<br>
<p>
Nobody is dearer than my mother<br>
Who always listens to what I say.<br>
No matter how busy i keep her<br>
She still cares for me in every way.<br>
<p>
Everyone wants me to be quiet.<br>
Everyone asks, "Where can peace be found?"<br>
But my mother never seems to mind at all.<br>
She is happy just to have me around.<br>
<p>
I remember the days when i was sick.<br>
I learned then even an angel can be tired.<br>
But she still appeared whenever i called her<br>
And her hands wiped my tears whenever i cried.<br>
<p>
"What is it like if there is no mother?"<br>
This is a most frightening thought!<br>
Just let me ask you one question in reply:<br>
"What is it like if there is no God?"<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
   MY PRAYER<br>
<p>
I do not pray that my days ahead,<br>
Be peaceful and free from burden;<br>
I only pray that Your will be done,<br>
In my life as it is in heaven.<br>
<p>
I do not pray that i will become,<br>
A depository of Your grace from above;<br>
I'd rather that You will make me<br>
A channel for Your matchless love.<br>
<p>
Oh God, open my ears and my eyes,<br>
To hear Your voice and to see Your face;<br>
Oh God, open my heart and my hands<br>
That i may the needy embrace.<br>
<p>
You have been my Creator and Saviour,<br>
And my guide since my birth;<br>
I pray that throughout eternity<br>
I will walk with you as i do on earth.<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
 		    HIS HANDS<br>
<p>
       They Sprinkled stars on the Milky Way.<br>
      They poured water into the restless seas.<br>
    They looked so tiny when in the manger He lay.<br>
   They planed and chiselled for a carpenter was He.<br>
They broke the loaves and fishes and thousands were fed.<br>
 They streatched out and touched the man with leprosy.<br>
     Then one day on a wooden cross they were laid;<br>
       There they were nailed for you and for me.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
