<!-- body="start" -->
One idea which I have had about a separate "niche" for SDA-L would be<br>
more of a news bulletin board than discussion items.  For example, if<br>
there were some piece of latebreaking news on this campus, someone can<br>
run to the computer rather than to the telephone to call Silver Spring<br>
and Loma Linda!  In many ways, being unmoderated would be an<br>
advantage--not to spread false information but so that it is clear that<br>
the writer is responsible for its accuracy.<br>
<p>
Another possibility, would be to have SDA-L concentrate on topics of<br>
specific interest to SDA higher education.  As more and more campuses<br>
get on the internet, this might be of importance to faculty and<br>
students.  It used to be that SDA faculty at these institutions met<br>
every 4 to 5 years to discuss common problems.  Because of financial<br>
retraints, these meetings no longer occur.  Perhaps we can continue them<br>
in an electronic forum.<br>
<p>
Just some ideas to think about.<br>
<p>
Harvey Brenneise<br>
(brneise@andrews.edu)<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
