As a rider to Steve's comments on "Adult Children" in the church:<br>
<p>
I have often wondered why the church tends to attract "odd" people.  I <br>
propose it is because of one of two reasons:<br>
<p>
     1.  Odd people are made to feel welcome in our church environment.<br>
<p>
     2.  Our message is sold in such a way that it is attractive to odd<br>
         people.<br>
<p>
What bothers me, is that I havn't worked out yet which one it is!<br>
<p>
Or are there other reasons?<br>
<p>
Maranatha<br>
<p>
Cecil<br>
