<title>May_1993: The Branch Davidians &amp; Events at Waco</title>
<h1>The Branch Davidians &amp; Events at Waco</h1>
Terry L Anderson 908-582-7013 (<i>tla@mozart.att.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 12 May 93 14:07:34 EDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#69">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#69">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#69">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#69">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0070.html">John Ash - CS: "Sabbath Observance"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0068.html">Vice-Dean Jerry Wiley - x06473: "Re: Authoritarian leadership"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
The Greater New York Adventist Forum Chapter (which meets at Columbia<br>
University, Manhattan), had an interesting meeting this past Sabbath.<br>
In the afternoon we had a discussion lead by Kendra Haloviak (Religion<br>
Dept Columbia Union College) with assistance from Roy Branson (editor<br>
of Spectrum).  After reviewing some of the event in Waco and telling<br>
reactions of some they knew that had relatives in the compound at<br>
Waco, they posed three questions.  I thought that perhaps some of you<br>
would find the questions interesting ponder.<br>
<p>
1.  What would you say were the primary differences between<br>
    traditional Seventh-day Adventism and the Branch Davidians?<br>
<p>
2.  What would you say were the primary similarities between<br>
    traditional Seventh-day Adventism and the Branch Davidians?<br>
<p>
3.  What lessons should we personally and the SDA church learn from<br>
    the experiences at Waco?<br>
<p>
We spend a very interesting 2 hours discussing these.  I will not<br>
attempt to give you a summary of the discussion -- it is most valuable<br>
to answer attempt your own answers anyway rather than hear those of<br>
others, but to get you started here is one of my own set of partial<br>
answers.<br>
<p>
#2: Similarities: I think that Seventh-day Adventism and the Davidians<br>
    share a similar basic apocalypticism.  Each believe that current<br>
    events should be viewed as part of a cosmic drama leading to the<br>
    end of current history.  I don't know enough about Branch Davidian<br>
    beliefs to know which details differ.<br>
<p>
#1: Differences: I think that our responses to apocalyptic events<br>
    differ.  Growing up in the church, I was presented with images<br>
    from Matthew of "running to the hills", of possible martyrdom, of<br>
    standing up before judges and defending our beliefs, of being<br>
    especially careful to make right decisions as probation might have<br>
    closed, but it was never suggested that Adventists might hole up<br>
    in a compound under siege and physically defend ourselves with<br>
    ammunition.<br>
<p>
#3: Lessons:  Perhaps, Seventh-day Adventists have spent too much<br>
    effort on teaching its members on how to recognize last day events<br>
    and too little on how to respond to them.<br>
<p>
Try some answers for yourself.<br>
<p>
<p>
			     --	Terry L Anderson<br>
				AT&amp;T Bell Laboratories, RM 3D-481<br>
				600 Mountain Av, Murray Hill, NJ 07974<br>
				UUCP:	...!att!mozart!tla<br>
				NET:	tla@mozart.att.com<br>
				ATTMAIL: mozart!tla<br>
				VOICE: 908 582-7013<br>
				FAX:   908 582-7988<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
