[CHURMS@nacdh4.nac.ac.za writes:]<br>
<i>&gt; I have often wondered why the church tends to attract "odd" people.  I </i><br>
<i>&gt; propose it is because of one of two reasons:</i><br>
<i>&gt;      1.  Odd people are made to feel welcome in our church environment.</i><br>
<i>&gt;      2.  Our message is sold in such a way that it is attractive to odd</i><br>
<i>&gt;          people.</i><br>
<p>
I genuinely doubt that SDA churches attract a disproportionate share of<br>
odd people.  I suspect one would find that other churches have their<br>
share as well.  As an extreme, perhaps, consider the "holiness" churches<br>
that handle rattlesnakes.  Consider the churches that pray for the death<br>
of certain Supreme Court justices whom they dislike.  Consider the churches<br>
that take racist or violent positions.  Etc, etc.<br>
