I like Harvey Brenneise's idea of using SDA-L as some kind of forum for<br>
discussion of items of interest to SDA higher education, or SDA's and<br>
higher education. We do miss the association amongst colleagues a lot. I<br>
think that the stated reason of reduced finances is purely a screen.<br>
Administrators still meet together.<br>
<p>
They may indeed be afraid that if faculty meet together on a broad basis<br>
they may start demanding some reasonable things like reversing the<br>
continued erosion of faculty salaries against inflation.<br>
<p>
Everybody probably knows, but if you haven't had your ear to the<br>
grapevine, The board of trustees of La Sierra University has invited Larry<br>
Geraty to leave AUC and come to LSU as president. Tom Mostert, board chairman,<br>
announced this at the faculty-board dinner after board meeting Monday<br>
night. Interstingly, in his announcement, Mostert never once mentioned<br>
Geraty's name! The debate is whether this was merely an oversight on<br>
Mostert's part, or a shrewd political maneuver to cover his tail if Geraty<br>
doesn't ever get here.<br>
<p>
Wil Clarke--Math LSU<br>
wclarke@polaris.lasierra.edu<br>
