Quite some months back, I posed a question to the net regarding how<br>
one might obtain materials produced by the late James Arrabito and<br>
his (now widowed) wife (sorry, I don't know here name).  I didn't<br>
get any responses, altho I noticed a passing reference by Dave Buxton<br>
in my collection of SDAnet postings.<br>
<p>
FYI, I tracked down the info, thanks to Steve Caza at Weimar:<br>
    LLT Productions<br>
    P.O. Box 205<br>
    Angwin, CA  94508<br>
    phone: 707-965-2786<br>
<p>
When I called this morning, the person answering mentioned several things<br>
of interest from which I can just recall two video titles:<br>
    A Young Person's History of the Sabbath<br>
    Israel of the Alps<br>
<p>
My eldest has seen the first and highly recommends it.  The second is about<br>
the Waldenses, a subject of great interest to my wife, Kathie.  Since<br>
SDAnetters might also find these subjects of interest for themselves or<br>
their church's video lending library, I reckoned I should share it.<br>
<pre>
