<title>May_1993: female homosexuality in the bible?</title>
<h1>female homosexuality in the bible?</h1>
TANG BENG YONG (<i>med10014@nusunix2.nus.sg</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 13 May 93 20:35:45 +0800</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#83">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#83">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#83">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#83">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0084.html">Steven Timm: "Re: The Branch Davidians &amp; Events at Waco"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0082.html">Steven Timm: "Re: E-mail addresses"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0088.html">Steven Timm: "Re: female homosexuality in the bible?"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Hello SDAnetters,<br>
<p>
	one of my classmates has been using irc to get into internet<br>
discussion groups, and he met this homosexual pastor from the USA who<br>
convinced him that the bible is not against homosexuality at all, and that<br>
people who say it does are interpreting it from a homophobic viewpoint. He<br>
is so convinced by this gay pastor that he has an almost missionary zeal to<br>
bring the other christians in my class around to his view.<br>
	I shall not go into the details of his arguments for biblical<br>
non-condemnation of homosexuality, no true SDA would ever be taken in by<br>
them. However, he brought up the point that the bible doesn't even mention<br>
anything about female homosexuality at all, and so it is at least ok to be<br>
lesbian. Well, i'v looked but i can't find anything in the bible that<br>
specifically makes any reference to female homosexuality. I'd be grateful if<br>
anyone can tell me if any such bible texts do exist, in case i missed it or<br>
something, so that if they do exist, i can show them to him.<br>
	Frankly, i cannot understand how anybody can come to the conclusion<br>
that the bible supports homosexuality, or how a homosexual can be a pastor.<br>
By the way, I recently herd from this advocate of erroneous doctrine, that<br>
Hawii may soon recognise homosexual marriages! That just blows my mind. I<br>
mean, isn't it illegal or something? Well i don't know about Hawii, but in<br>
my country it is illegal to have sex with children or with members of the<br>
same sex, and such practices are generally regarded with disgust and<br>
abhorrence, even by the majority non-christian population.<br>
<p>
-beng<br>
