<title>May_1993: Re: The Branch Davidians &amp; Events at Waco</title>
<h1>Re: The Branch Davidians &amp; Events at Waco</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 14 May 1993 01:02:35 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#84">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#84">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#84">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#84">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0085.html">Tony Dyson: "Re: Sabbath"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0083.html">TANG BENG YONG: "female homosexuality in the bible?"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0099.html">Terry L Anderson 908-582-7013: "The Branch Davidians &amp; Events at Waco"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0129.html">Steve Hix: "Re: The Branch Davidians &amp; Events at Waco"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Differences between the Davidians?<br>
<p>
Well, my mother went to school with Desmond Doss and so I grew up on<br>
Desmond Doss stories.  Desmond Doss served as a medic in WW-II, keeping<br>
the Sabbath and refusing to carry a weapon.  On training maneuvers<br>
on Sabbath he stayed at the base reading his Bible.  Because of his<br>
honest sincere hardworking courage he soon was accepted by the troops<br>
after a few weeks of harrasment.  The high point of the book comes<br>
when his unit takes on the Japanese in one of the bloodiest battles,<br>
on the Sabbath.  This was not war games, medics were going to be<br>
desperately needed and so Desmond Doss moved out with his unit with<br>
his medical kit.  The troops climbed a cliff and started forward<br>
and were soon mowed down by gun fire.  Those who had not made it over<br>
the top refused to go forward to retrieve the wounded.  Desmond Doss<br>
climbed that cliff with ropes and medical gear.  He dragged his buddies<br>
back to the top of the cliff and then had to stand up, exposed to<br>
gun fire, to lower each man by rope to his buddies down below.  The<br>
bullets whistled past his ears but not one his him.  He was later<br>
awarded the Congressional Medal of Honor by the president of the USA<br>
on the White House lawn.<br>
<p>
In all the Apocaliptic scenarios I've read about SDAs in a last<br>
days context, I don't see any of them picking up anything to defend<br>
themselves.<br>
<p>
SDAs -- non compatent medics in time of war.<br>
[I think that ^^^^ means _combatant_.  SCT]<br>
<p>
Branch Davidians -- amasing an arsinal of war.<br>
<p>
DaveB<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
