final break between branch members and the official SDA church was<br>
pacifism -- early in WW II, they objected to the SDA position of<br>
conscientious "cooperation" or non-combatency, preferring a completely<br>
pacifist position.  If this is true, the evolution to one of armed<br>
resistence is particularly ironic.<br>
