<!-- body="start" -->
[TANG BENG YONG writes:]<br>
<i>&gt; anything about female homosexuality at all, and so it is at least ok to be</i><br>
<i>&gt; lesbian. Well, i'v looked but i can't find anything in the bible that</i><br>
<i>&gt; specifically makes any reference to female homosexuality. I'd be grateful if</i><br>
<p>
Definitely Rom 1:26,27; possibly 2 Tim 3:2,3 or Jude 10 and thereabouts.<br>
<p>
Regarding heterosexual relationships, as Steve T, brought up, the KJV reads:<br>
    HEB 13:4 Marriage is honourable in all, and the bed undefiled: but<br>
    whoremongers and adulterers God will judge.<br>
Some have concluded that Paul is saying "anything goes, if you're married",<br>
thereby justifying oral, anal, a bit of bondage or porn, S&amp;M, etc (gross!).<br>
<p>
I have read that the KJV rendering is unfortunate, that the underlying<br>
Greek is more like an injunction, "Keep your marriage bed undefiled!"<br>
(Perhaps those who actually know Greek can help out.  I don't have other<br>
translations at hand, so I'll have to check how they read.)  In my reading<br>
of EGW, I have come across counsel that certain behaviors *do* defile the<br>
marriage bed.<br>
<p>
Regarding Lordship and God's purposes, if you enjoy studying Scripture<br>
to see how it matches with what you've heretofore believe, I recommend<br>
a book from Wolgemuth &amp; Hyatt publishers, by Rick &amp; Jan Hess, entitled<br>
"A Full Quiver".  If you think you know what Ps 127:3-5 means, this will<br>
challenge you.  It sure did us.<br>
