<!-- body="start" -->
When discussing the existence of homo-sexuality (male and female) in relation<br>
to biblical teaching, I have often wondered if it would not be wise to <br>
"back up" one step:<br>
<p>
Would someone with these type of "propensities" be willing to make a<br>
"till-death-do-us-part" commitment with one and only one partner?  If not,<br>
wouldn't it be unacceptable on these biblical grounds?<br>
<p>
Phrased differently, when Christ said a look accompanied by desire for any-<br>
one other than one's wife constituted adultery, wouldn't a desiring look<br>
at someone of the same sex (if the person has such desires), also be<br>
breaking of the 7th commandment.  Christ's words obviously apply to ladies<br>
desires towards men as well and hence I would see in Matthew 5 a biblical<br>
basis for rejecting 99% of typical homo-sexual practices.<br>
<p>
Maranatha<br>
<p>
Cecil (CHURMS@NACDH4.NAC.AC.ZA)<br>
