<title>May_1993: Thought...</title>
<h1>Thought...</h1>
Marcus Stringer (<i>marcuss@microsoft.com</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 17 May 93 12:40:25 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#112">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#112">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#112">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#112">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0113.html">Malachi Robertson: "OT Laws and You"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0111.html">Marcus Stringer: "re: female homosexuality in the bible?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In my most recent re-reading of the Desire of Ages (today) I found a<br>
thought which I'd not dwelt on before.  Sister White describes in<br>
chapter 14 (We have found the Messias) the scene with Jesus<br>
meeting John the Baptist in the wilderness as he preaches and the<br>
beginning of Jesus' gathering of his disciples.  She writes:<br>
-------------- 0 --------------<br>
"If Nathanael had trusted in the rabbis for guidance, he would never<br>
have found Jesus.  It was by seeing and judging for himself that he<br>
became a disciple.  So in the case of many today whom prejudice<br>
witholds from good.  How different would be the result, if they would<br>
'come and see.'  While they trust in the guidance of human authority,<br>
none will come to a saving knowledge of the truth.  ....Philip said to<br>
Nathanael, 'Come and see.'  He did not ask him to accept another's<br>
testimony, but to behold Christ for himself.  Now that Jesus has<br>
ascended to heaven, His disciples are His representatives among<br>
men, and one of the most effective ways of winning souls to Him is in<br>
exemplifying His character in our daily life.  Our influence upon others<br>
depends not so much upon what we say, as upon what we are.<br>
Men may combat and defy our logic, they may resist our appeals;<br>
but a life of disinterested love is an argument they cannot gainsay.<br>
A consistent life, characterized by the meekness of Christ, is a power<br>
in the world."<br>
-------------- 0 --------------<br>
This is pretty encouraging to me!  For millennia, the people of God had<br>
to approach through sacrifice, and earthly priest, now the only door<br>
to God is Jesus Christ the righteous.  And more, we are welcomed to<br>
"come and see"  ***for ourselves***.  We are free to approach God in<br>
Christ just as we are (don't have to pretend to be something/someone<br>
you aren't)!  We can be honest and open with our savior!  Isn't this GOOD<br>
NEWS?<br>
<p>
Marcus Stringer<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
