<title>May_1993: Request for prayer support</title>
<h1>Request for prayer support</h1>
TANG BENG YONG (<i>med10014@nusunix2.nus.sg</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 17 May 93 14:07:31 +0800</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#117">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#117">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#117">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#117">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0118.html">Steven Timm: "Bargain time at the Den O'Thieves"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0116.html">Maurice George Ashton: "Re: Sabbath Observance"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Dear brothers and sisters in Christ,<br>
<p>
	one of our people, namely my friend Caleb Khor Ken Swee, who is an<br>
AY leader in my church, has need of your prayers.  He is a first year<br>
engineering student at the Nanyang Technological University (NTU) here in<br>
Singapore.  He just got his examination time table, and his computing paper<br>
is scheduled to be sat for at 9am on Saturday 5th June.  This is quite a<br>
trying situation for him as his career is at stake here.  He is trying to<br>
contact the registrar's office to see if anything can be done to arrange for<br>
him to sit for the paper on another day, i have not had news yet of what has<br>
come of that.<br>
	As you probably know, Sabbath problems are no fun at all, so please<br>
pray the Lord to give him faith and guidance. If you want to give him some<br>
encouraging words, send them to him at this address:<br>
<p>
	be7116503@ntuvax.ntu.ac.sg<br>
<p>
OR<br>
<p>
	be7116503@v9000.ntu.ac.sg<br>
<p>
regards,<br>
	Beng Tang<br>
