I wouldn't recommend this book to anyone eho isn't an SDA.  It basically <br>
makes E.G. White into a plagarist.  Maybe by today's legal standards, she <br>
could be charged with plagarism, but back in the 19th century, you didn't <br>
have to document your sources as thoughly as you do now.<br>
If Sister White had broken any plagarism laws, she would've been brought <br>
to trial, I'm sure.  Since she wasn't sued or ever accused of plagarism <br>
by her detractors in her day, I'd have to say that Walter Rea was out to <br>
smear Sister White, not to encourage the remnant church in the faith of <br>
Jesus.<br>
<p>
Tammy<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
