<!-- body="start" -->
Lola's mention of the Newbury Park shopping development<br>
begs further information, but if it really happens, it will be <br>
by no means unprecedented.  A few years ago the Lake <br>
Region conference tried to develop a shopping center<br>
on the south side of Chicago, with poor financial results,<br>
and their conference president was forced out of office<br>
over the issue.<br>
<p>
None of you thought that an SDA college would sell out to <br>
the conservatives.  But here we go selling out to real estate<br>
developers.  When will we ever learn?  More and more I'm <br>
realizing the blessing of having a local church which is in <br>
fine financial shape.  Any conferences looking for a <br>
Stewardship secretary should contact our current pastor,<br>
I will supply his name on request.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
