<title>May_1993: Update on the organ search</title>
<h1>Update on the organ search</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 17 May 1993 19:31:30 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#120">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#120">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#120">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#120">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0121.html">Steve Hix: "Re: Newbury Park shopping mall"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0119.html">Steven Timm: "Homosexuality"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
A few weeks ago I wrote about our local church situation<br>
and the supposed controversy over a potential new organ.<br>
It appears that I misrepresented the career, the attitude,<br>
the position, and the competence of one of the key players.<br>
He's not a dentist, but a nutritionist, and he was never for<br>
getting the Wurlitzer organ as I accused him of being. <br>
I apologize for the errors.<br>
<p>
Cooler heads have prevailed, but he has proven to be one <br>
of them.  An organ committee was formed, and they are going to do a very<br>
responsible job of evaluating the leading makes of organs, with an<br>
emphasis on buying quality.  A fund-raising plan will also come into<br>
play.  <br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
