<title>May_1993: Century of Adventist Education in South Africa</title>
<h1>Century of Adventist Education in South Africa</h1>
Wil Clarke (<i>wclarke@polaris.lasierra.edu</i>)<br>
<i>18 May 1993 15:04:25 -0600</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#137">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#137">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#137">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#137">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0138.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re:  female homosexuality in the bible?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0136.html">TANG BENG YONG: "Re: Sabbath Observance"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Congratulations! Helderberg! for being the culmination of 100 years of SDA<br>
education in South Africa. We're proud of our association with you.<br>
<p>
Here are some prospective goals for the second century:<br>
1.  Obtain a charter for Helderberg--achieve recognized South African<br>
accreditation.<br>
2.  Meaningfully serve all South African Adventists regardless of race.<br>
3.  Achieve national and international recognition for academic<br>
excellence. (EGW: we are to be the head and not the tail!)<br>
4.  Pioneer innovative and effective techniques for bringing the gospel to<br>
the churched and unchurched.<br>
<p>
Best wishes for the future!<br>
Wil &amp; Sylvia Clarke<br>
and the Southern California Helderberg Alumni Chapter.<br>
<p>
Thanks Cecil, for being willing to communicate this with Helderberg!<br>
Greetings to Mandy and ABCD  :)<br>
Wil<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
