Isn't there a text that suggests that God's judgment of<br>
human conduct takes into account "that this man was born here<br>
and this one born there. . ."?  Might that not mean that God<br>
will take into account genetic differences?  Tendencies?<br>
<p>
If human justice can take into account privileges, justifications,<br>
and excuses to ameliorate the effects of conduct,  I wonder if<br>
God does?<br>
<p>
--Jerry Wiley<br>
