<!-- body="start" -->
I note the interest in organs but I don't know how the subject got<br>
started.  One thing that I am quite certain of is this, that the organ<br>
built during the 80's in the Collegedale, TN SDA church is the largest<br>
tracker organ built in the U.S. in the 20th century.  It is both wonderful<br>
to hear and a visual delight.  A second special tracker organ was built<br>
for the music recital hall at Southern College and a third small tracker<br>
for the studio of organist Judy Glass.  All three organs were build by<br>
John Brombaugh (sp?).  All of these organs were built in the tracker (the<br>
keys are mechanically attached to each pipe) style but with such modern<br>
touches such as teflon bushings where tracks were attached to each other.  A<br>
formal concert in the church is something not to be missed.<br>
<p>
Good listening to all.<br>
Bill Allen<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
