<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; If the BATF figures are to be believed, the original warrent</i><br>
<i>&gt; estimated roughly one rifle per member...and I know people in</i><br>
<i>&gt; my church that exceed that number.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Rural communities are somewhat different than urban or suburban.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Even among SDA's.</i><br>
<p>
At one time, in Alaska, state law required that aircraft flying cross-country<br>
carry a firearm of a minimum size.  This included, of course, the church-owned<br>
aircraft.  It would not surprise me to learn that this requirement was still<br>
in force.  And besides: in Alaska, that makes a lot of sense.<br>
<p>
Any former Alaskan pastors care to comment on that?  :)<br>
<p>
--Bill Nickless<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
