<title>May_1993: Censored Newsgroups @ WWC</title>
<h1>Censored Newsgroups @ WWC</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 19 May 1993 18:59:22 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#145">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#145">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#145">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#145">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0146.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: Anti-evangelism"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0144.html">Sherman Cox: "Re: The Branch Davidians &amp; Events at Waco"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0173.html">Richard Behrens: "Re: Censored Newsgroups @ WWC"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[From John Ash]<br>
Hi all,<br>
<p>
   Well, no longer is there uncensored reading of newsgroups at WWC.  <br>
Evidently the administration finally got wind of all the "evils" which were<br>
available and made a quick &amp; decisive cut.  Here is the notice which was<br>
posted:<br>
<p>
<p>
<i>&gt; By order of C. Michael Bell and President Andreasen, the following</i><br>
newsgroups <br>
<i>&gt;   are no longer received on this campus.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; alt.politics.homosexuality</i><br>
<i>&gt; alt.sex</i><br>
<i>&gt; alt.sex.bondage</i><br>
<i>&gt; alt.sex.motss</i><br>
<i>&gt; alt.sex.movies</i><br>
<i>&gt; alt.sex.stories</i><br>
<i>&gt; alt.sexual.abuse.recovery</i><br>
<i>&gt; alt.sexual.abuse.recovery.d</i><br>
<i>&gt; alt.sex.fetish.feet</i><br>
<i>&gt; alt.sex.extropians</i><br>
<i>&gt; alt.sex.bestiality.barney</i><br>
<i>&gt; alt.satanism</i><br>
<i>&gt; bit.listserv.gaynet</i><br>
<i>&gt; rec.nude</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Any discussion of or disagreements with any of this list should be sent to </i><br>
<i>&gt;   C. Michael Bell (bellmi).  The president is forming a committee to</i><br>
look into<br>
<i>&gt;   the matter.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; P.S. The news administrator on this machine was not part of this</i><br>
decision.  No<br>
<i>&gt;   flames to ashted, please.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; --</i><br>
<i>&gt; Ted Ashton  (ashted@wwc.edu)</i><br>
<i>&gt; Campus Computer Center   (509) 527-2307</i><br>
<i>&gt; Walla Walla College                         </i><br>
<p>
(For your information, Michael Bell (bellmi@wwc.edu) is the head of the <br>
Campus Computer Center.)<br>
<p>
<p>
   Just a few comments.  It's interesting to look at the above list and<br>
attempt to understand the rationale behind the cuts.  For example, why did <br>
they choose (apparently) to cut ALL groups having to do with SEX and/or <br>
HOMOSEXUALITY, while leaving groups such as alt.tasteless.penis?<br>
<p>
   Maybe that's what the committee is looking into...<br>
<p>
--John Ash (jash@eecs.wsu.edu) <br>
KB7ONG  <br>
[If they only knew how many they missed....  :-)  SCT]<br>
