<!-- body="start" -->
It seems as though there are so many concerns about the "White Lie" by<br>
Walter Rae.  I have never seen this man in person, but I have heard a lot<br>
about him, and I have seen his book.  When I started to read it, I have<br>
discovered that I will waste my time reading it, and there are other<br>
important books to read than this one.<br>
<p>
Whatever he wrote about Ellen G. White, let him believe the way he does,<br>
but for me I truly believe that Mrs. White was the chosen prophet of God, and<br>
that ALL her writings were inspired.<br>
<p>
Every time I read her books, I am always feel inspired and uplifted by<br>
them.  But she also warned us that we should not put  <br>
her writings above the Word of God.  The Bible is the greater light, and her<br>
writings are the lesser light that makes us understand the greater light.<br>
Sometimes it's a waste of time to discuss issues like this.  Our hope is<br>
to see Jesus, and to prepare our lives for heaven.  Only when we allow the<br>
Holy Spirit to guide us, that we will find the truth, but whatever<br>
controversy that is going on in our church, all have to do with human<br>
understanding, and their own interpretation, because THE SPIRIT ONLY LEAD<br>
US TO ALL TRUTH, not to SOME, but to ALL TRUTH.  <br>
<p>
We have also received at James White Library a book written by a former<br>
adventist couple who were both brought up in an adventist home, and both<br>
attended our adventist institutes, taught at one of our Academies, but<br>
once the husband read this book, he believed it, and left the  church, and<br>
he's been attacking the church ever since.  He belongs to another<br>
denomination, and said that he has never been so rich since he left the<br>
Seventh-day Adventist church.  So I encourage everyone that if you based<br>
your opinion on someone else's without seeking the guidance of the Spirit,<br>
you will be lead astray.  (This book is in the Adventist Heritage Center)<br>
<p>
Please pray for one another, and those who have left the church so one of<br>
these days they will understand.  Also pray that the Holy Spirit will give<br>
us decernment in order to understand His Word fully!<br>
<p>
Gingerlei Tupito<br>
Staff, James White Library<br>
Andrews University<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
