<title>May_1993: Spring Lectureship - All Nations Church</title>
<h1>Spring Lectureship - All Nations Church</h1>
Gingerlei Tupito (<i>tupito@edmund.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 20 May 1993 09:21:49 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#174">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#174">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#174">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#174">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0175.html">Daniel Turk: "Collegedale Church organ"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0173.html">Richard Behrens: "Re: Censored Newsgroups @ WWC"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I would like to announce that The All Nations Seventh-day Adventist Church<br>
at 4259 East Snow Road in Berrien Springs, MI will hold a Spring<br>
Lectureship series this weekend, Friday, May 21, at 7:30 p.m. and Sabbath,<br>
May 22 at 11:00 a.m. and 3:00 p.m.  The Special guest speaker is DR. ROY<br>
BRANSON, he's the editor for the SPECTRUM megazine, and also widely<br>
known both within and outside Adventist circles as a theologian, ethicist,<br>
lecturer, and writer.<br>
<p>
The theme of his series is:  "Fire In The Mirror: Adventism After Ranch<br>
Apocalypse.<br>
<p>
Friday evening - 7:30 p.m.  he will speak on "Weeping Until The Day Dawn: <br>
1844-Waco."<br>
<p>
Sabbath Morning 11:00 am. he will speak on "Out of The Ambers:  The City<br>
of God."<br>
<p>
Sabbath Afternoon 3:00 p.m. he will speak on "Beyond The Compound To The<br>
City of God."<br>
<p>
A panel discussion will follow after the 3pm meeting.  The panelists are:<br>
<p>
	George Knight<br>
	Jaspine Bilima<br>
	Sally Andriamiarisoa<br>
	Oystein Labiaka<br>
<p>
All those who are around the area, please come and bring a friend.<br>
<p>
Thank you,  may you all have a wonderful Sabbath!<br>
<p>
Gingerlei<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
