<title>May_1993: Only conservative dresses</title>
<h1>Only conservative dresses</h1>
TracyAnne Burtch-Nickless (<i>burtch@abby.mcs.anl.gov</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 20 May 93 17:42:12 CDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#168">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#168">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#168">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#168">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0169.html">David Plaisted: "Re: Southern College's Organ"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0167.html">David Plaisted: "Re: The White Lie,"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I have a friend who is a new Seventh-day Adventist christian. I will call her <br>
Mary.  She was converted about three years ago.  She is very on fire for the <br>
Lord and is going about witnessing with great zeal.  She recently became <br>
convicted by God that women are to wear conservative dresses.  This means<br>
that only conservative dresses are to be worn, slacks are not ok to <br>
wear regardless of the circumtance.  There was a work bee to clear land for <br>
a new church and school, and Mary came in a dress.<br>
 <br>
I have another friend, that I will call Sue.  She is a much newer <br>
Seventh-day Adventist christian.  Both friends go to the same church.  Mary <br>
is going about convicting Sue that she also should only wear conservative <br>
dresses.<br>
  <br>
Sue doen't really believe this, but doesn't know how to refute what<br>
Mary says, especially when Mary backs it up with the Bible and Mrs White.<br>
(I do not know the passages used).  Sue recently gave away a pretty<br>
dress, that did not meet all of Mary's criteria, but is regretful that she <br>
did.  <br>
 <br>
Sue wants to do what is right and to know what God wants for her to do.<br>
 <br>
I would like to know if those on SDAnet know of any references in the<br>
Bible or in what Ellen White has written that could give Sue some<br>
guidance.   <br>
<p>
Thanks much<br>
 TracyAnne Nickless<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
