<p>
Mark Fuller (acus10@waccvm.corp.mot.com) uploaded 6.00 to<br>
wuarchive (128.252.135.4) in /doc/bible/ibm-pc and keeps it fairly<br>
up-to-date.  Someone recently uploaded most if not all to simtel20<br>
(192.88.110.20), so it should also appear soon on simtel20 mirror sites.<br>
I recall a comment in 5.00 that a French version was forth-coming,<br>
but I've not heard more.  Mark would know since he has regular<br>
contact with Larry Price (Mr OLB).<br>
<p>
Someone mentioned in soc.religion.christian.bible-study a couple<br>
months back that the AV text provided is Webster's and differs<br>
slightly from the typical KJV.  Ring a bell with anybody?  I've<br>
been tripped up by specifying American vs British spellings a few<br>
times in searches.  The AV text is typically bundled with Darby's.<br>
I believe Darby was Plymouth Brethren, so perhaps he might render<br>
some texts to fit his eschatology (futurist, I think?).<br>
