<i>&gt; &gt; alt.sex.bestiality.barney</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; alt.satanism</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; bit.listserv.gaynet</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; rec.nude</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; Any discussion of or disagreements with any of this list should be sent to </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;   C. Michael Bell (bellmi).  The president is forming a committee to</i><br>
<i>&gt; look into</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;   the matter.</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; P.S. The news administrator on this machine was not part of this</i><br>
<i>&gt; decision.  No</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;   flames to ashted, please.</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; --</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; Ted Ashton  (ashted@wwc.edu)</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; Campus Computer Center   (509) 527-2307</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; Walla Walla College                         </i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; (For your information, Michael Bell (bellmi@wwc.edu) is the head of the </i><br>
<i>&gt; Campus Computer Center.)</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt;    Just a few comments.  It's interesting to look at the above list and</i><br>
<i>&gt; attempt to understand the rationale behind the cuts.  For example, why did </i><br>
<i>&gt; they choose (apparently) to cut ALL groups having to do with SEX and/or </i><br>
<i>&gt; HOMOSEXUALITY, while leaving groups such as alt.tasteless.penis?</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt;    Maybe that's what the committee is looking into...</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; --John Ash (jash@eecs.wsu.edu) </i><br>
<i>&gt; KB7ONG  </i><br>
<i>&gt; [If they only knew how many they missed....  :-)  SCT]</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<p>
While I cannot tell John that he was wrong to have posted this to SDANet, I<br>
can say that I would have appreciated a little more thinking and discussion<br>
before he did.  I, personally, was not involved in the making of this decision,<br>
however, as news administrator, I was the one to implement the policy.  I know<br>
from talking with those who made the list that the choices shown above are <br>
neither long-thought-through, nor permanent.  The group neither includes all <br>
which will be cut, nor excludes all which will be left.  That, in particular, <br>
IS what the committee is looking into.  So, please, realize this before telling <br>
us just how wrong our current choices are (either inclusions or exclusions).  <br>
<pre>
-- 
Ted Ashton  (ashted@wwc.edu)
Campus Computer Center   (509) 527-2307
Walla Walla College                         
