Sherman writes:<br>
<p>
I believe something is wrong when we derive pleasure from the subjigation of<br>
an opponent.  The spirit of Jesus is to build up others.  To want the best for<br>
                                                                        <br>
                                   ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^<br>
others.  To even give up your life for others.  Is the spirit of competition<br>
^^^^^<br>
compatible with that?  I believe that is the question.<br>
==============<br>
You ask an excellent question Sherman.  It's a question which leads, I think,<br>
to "the mission field", right here in America.  AMERICA, a nation so <br>
firmly rooted<br>
in competition.<br>
<p>
Again, we see that Jesus' way goes completely OPPOSITE from us and our ways...<br>
And as Steve says, "When will we ever learn?"<br>
<p>
Marcus<br>
