<title>May_1993: Re: Censored Newsgroups @ WWC</title>
<h1>Re: Censored Newsgroups @ WWC</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Sat, 22 May 1993 19:26:42 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#235">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#235">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#235">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#235">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0236.html">Ron Estrada: "Re: EGW question, reply to Tony Dyson"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0234.html">Marcus Stringer: "RE: Competition"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0145.html">Steven Timm: "Censored Newsgroups @ WWC"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0271.html">Alvin Vitangcol: "Re: Censored Newsgroups @ WWC"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
 From Alvin Vitangcol<br>
<p>
As the name suggests, ASAR is a public forum on recovery from all types of<br>
sexual abuse, including rape experienced by adults as well as by children.  It<br>
is frequented by both males and females, and is accessible to everyone,<br>
including supporters, health care professionals, perpetrators, and the general<br>
public.  The cast of readers and authors changes constantly.  Recently<br>
discussed topics include self-inflicted violence, multiple personalities,<br>
confronting/naming perpetrators, dealing with the holidays, explaining oneself<br>
to prying members of the general public, self-defense, nightmares, etc.<br>
<p>
I just took a quick look at alt.sexual.abuse.recovery.  It seems to<br>
follow the fate of several of the alt newsgroups.  It IS a support<br>
group, but it tends to shoot off into the bizzare.  Plus, a lot of the<br>
posts seemed like they were more interested in flaming people than<br>
actually discussing.  One other thing is that the posters appear to be<br>
more interested in finding out exactly what happened, but are less<br>
interested in actually discussing the topic.<br>
<p>
**********************<br>
<p>
<p>
I think a key factor in eliminating this newsgroup though, comes from<br>
the following section of the FAQ:<br>
<p>
Judgements of sexual behavior should not be made.  ASAR readers run the gamut<br>
from heterosexual to homosexual and everything in between.  No matter what your<br>
orientation is, you have as much right as anyone to participate in ASAR, and as<br>
little right to criticize someone else's sexuality as you would give to them.<br>
<p>
***********************<br>
<p>
I think the preceding statement does justify the canceling of this<br>
newsgroup, in that WWC is trying to get rid of newsgroups which<br>
contradict the beliefs of SDA's.<br>
<p>
I wrote a message several weeks ago on what I thought about the<br>
newsgroup situation, but after talking to several people, it doesn't<br>
seem to have been posted.  Can anyone tell me if they saw it, or else if<br>
not, I'll post it again?<br>
<pre>
-- 
$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$
$
<p>
	    %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
	    %% Alvin Vitangcol - "YES IT IS I, THE REAL CHIPMUNK %%
	    %%      Andrews University (vitanga@andrews.edu)     %%
	    %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
<p>
Only beautiful women who are engaged or engaged to be engaged or married or
your mother's best friend will think that you are a wonderful person
that any   
woman would die for.
<p>
A "Taken" woman will tell you that you are a great-looking guy, but that looks 
don't matter anyway and that she'd go out with you if she wasn't already
dating someone.
<p>
Any woman that you become extremely attracted to will tell you that you are 
the best friend that a woman could ever have.
<p>
$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$
$
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
