<title>May_1993: Re: Price gouging on veggie-meat?</title>
<h1>Re: Price gouging on veggie-meat?</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Sat, 22 May 1993 19:43:36 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#208">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#208">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#208">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#208">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0209.html">Bruce Holm: "Re: sdas and guns"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0207.html">Ralf Simonsson: "&gt; Spring Lectureship - All Nations Church"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0187.html">a11111arne@attmail.com: "Re: Price gouging on veggie-meat?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[I might have sent out twice the post to which Dan is replying,<br>
so I will delete the entire body of that message which he included.<br>
Go easy on the included text, folks. Some of us (including me) have disk <br>
quotas.  SCT]<br>
<p>
<p>
Yes, I realize that this type of thing is done many places and that it<br>
is probably done in this situation.  What amazes me is that in the<br>
"vege-meat" market and in our book market it appears that we charge<br>
quite a bit more than what the "normal" market would bear.  And that if<br>
we would enlarge our market and distribution systems we would be able to<br>
increase our volume, decrease our prices, and probably earn more<br>
overall.  It continually amazes me when I go into other Christian book<br>
stores and then compare those prices with the prices of ABC's.  I have<br>
long thought that we (SDA book publishers) should make our books<br>
available in the wider Christian bookstore market, and that we could<br>
then increase volume and decrease prices... and reach many more people!<br>
<p>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
Dan Turk     Computer Science &amp; Information Systems     Andrews University<br>
Berrien Springs, MI          turk@andrews.edu               (616) 471-3426<br>
==========================================================================<br>
